Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:19.72,Default,,0,0,0,,What we have been doing is creating a context in which to hold an understanding of the whole process of addiction.\NAnd by the time we finish today, we'll see why the world has been relatively unsuccessful in handling the whole problem of addiction,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.46,0:00:33.30,Default,,0,0,0,,with the exception, of course, of Alcoholics Anonymous, which has been the only successful approach thus far.\NThe purpose is to create a context, a way of holding, a way of understanding,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.98,0:00:42.44,Default,,0,0,0,,because context is the most important thing in our life,\Nbecause out of context comes meaning, and out of meaning comes value,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.16,0:00:52.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and out of value comes goals, and therefore it really directs our entire life.\NThis kind of learning, which is not left brain learning,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.12,0:00:58.04,Default,,0,0,0,,the right brain learns by familiarity, by circling over the same material.\NSo?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.00,0:01:07.20,Default,,0,0,0,,The person who's listening to it this year is not the same person who listened to it last year.\NIn fact, to hear the material, you become a different person,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.34,0:01:16.23,Default,,0,0,0,,and so nobody will hear the same thing they heard last year.\NSo we'll recapitulate some of the things we said last year, and then we'll extend it.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:16.75,0:01:19.64,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll extend it.\NI apologize for the writing.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.40,0:01:27.03,Default,,0,0,0,,It is a typical doctor's writing.\NWe learned this at medical school.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:27.81,0:01:30.63,Default,,0,0,0,,And if your writing is legible, then you flunk.\NSo?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:30.63,0:01:36.57,Default,,0,0,0,,You get called into the dean's office.\NSo this is typical doctor's writing, and therefore I'll explain these terms
Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.57,0:01:47.35,Default,,0,0,0,,so that those of you who can't actually read it will hear it.\NIn the center is the box, and a lot of my talks, people in DeVille,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.45,0:01:58.09,Default,,0,0,0,,a lot of the former residents there refer to the box and where they are in the box.\NAnd so the box is really the ego as understood in psychology.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.81,0:02:06.96,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the self with a small s.\NIt's a lower mind, the common everyday mind with a small m.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.75,0:02:18.69,Default,,0,0,0,,The bottom of the box, we always start with the bottom of the box and work our way up.\NThe bottom of the box is a state, is an energy field.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.95,0:02:24.06,Default,,0,0,0,,In the center of the box, these are really energy fields.\NAnd energy fields are impersonal.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.58,0:02:30.24,Default,,0,0,0,,An energy field is impersonal.\NThose of you who have studied or heard of geomancy realize
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.00,0:02:38.70,Default,,0,0,0,,that an energy field in nature is impersonal.\NAnd therefore, these energy fields have labels and names,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.56,0:02:47.50,Default,,0,0,0,,but that's just the name of that energy field.\NTo the right of it is the emotion that comes out of that energy field.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.28,0:02:59.29,Default,,0,0,0,,And at the far right is the process going on in consciousness.\NIn the center, then, we have in the box these fields of consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.21,0:03:06.04,Default,,0,0,0,,And beginning at the bottom, we have guilt.\NGuilt, which you'll notice,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.18,0:03:12.74,Default,,0,0,0,,that is a reversed energy field.\NUnderneath the names of these various energy fields is an arrow,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.74,0:03:17.04,Default,,0,0,0,,which I would hope would be in a different color,\Nbut I forgot my pink chalk today.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.48,0:03:27.48,Default,,0,0,0,,You'll notice that there's a direction to the energy field,\Nand also there's a number which calibrates the relative energy of that energy field.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.65,0:03:35.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Starting with death, calibrated at zero.\NAnd this can be repeated by anyone,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.03,0:03:39.55,Default,,0,0,0,,and it has been repeated by many people.\NIt's been proven and verified.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.55,0:03:43.55,Default,,0,0,0,,If you start with death at zero,\Nyou will end up with enlightenment at 600,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.55,0:03:47.58,Default,,0,0,0,,what the world calls enlightenment.\NIt depends beyond duality.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.06,0:03:55.06,Default,,0,0,0,,If you start with death at zero,\Nyou will end up with 600 as the top of the box,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.06,0:04:02.06,Default,,0,0,0,,beyond which identification with the small self,\Nthe personal ego, is transcended.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.17,0:04:09.17,Default,,0,0,0,,At the bottom of the box, then, preceding death,\Nare two states, apathy and guilt.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.17,0:04:15.97,Default,,0,0,0,,You'll notice that in the middle,\Nyou'll notice that the energy field goes to the left.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.97,0:04:23.97,Default,,0,0,0,,The direction of the energy field indicates something extremely important.\NAll those energy fields below the level of courage,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.97,0:04:32.38,Default,,0,0,0,,which is a crucial level in the understanding of the addictions,\Nall the energy fields below courage are reversed.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.38,0:04:39.31,Default,,0,0,0,,All the levels below courage are reversed,\Nand they're all levels of victim.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.31,0:04:47.04,Default,,0,0,0,,They're all levels of having sold out.\NSo being close to death,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.04,0:04:53.04,Default,,0,0,0,,we see apathy calibrates at 50.\NWe see guilt calibrates at 30.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.04,0:05:00.07,Default,,0,0,0,,These states preceding death, we notice,\Nare accompanied by an emotional state of hopelessness,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.07,0:05:08.23,Default,,0,0,0,,of despondency, of despair, of depression.\NAnd as you slip into guilt itself,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.23,0:05:14.52,Default,,0,0,0,,self-hatred, the feeling of sin, worthlessness.\NAnd out of that comes
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.52,0:05:22.58,Default,,0,0,0,,the destruction due to the loss of energy.\NThat state of apathy, hopelessness, despondency,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.58,0:05:30.22,Default,,0,0,0,,which precedes death,\Nis a state in which the individual becomes de-energized.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.22,0:05:36.32,Default,,0,0,0,,They become de-energized\Nbecause the state right above it is dispirited.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.32,0:05:40.32,Default,,0,0,0,,The loss of the desire to live,\Nand because of that,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.32,0:05:45.32,Default,,0,0,0,,the loss of energy from the universe,\Nwhich the spirit, that which is life,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.32,0:05:52.27,Default,,0,0,0,,pulls into us.\NSo apathy is a state of great importance
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.27,0:05:58.30,Default,,0,0,0,,in the addictions.\NIt's a state of great importance in the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.30,0:06:05.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Probably a third of the world lives in a state of apathy.\NThirty percent, perhaps, of the world lives in a state of apathy,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.30,0:06:10.68,Default,,0,0,0,,hopelessness.\NTomorrow will not be any better than today.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.68,0:06:16.71,Default,,0,0,0,,The mothers in Ethiopia and Africa,\Nplaces like that,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.71,0:06:21.81,Default,,0,0,0,,stare, just stare blankly,\Nwatching the children's bellies swell up with starvation.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.81,0:06:27.10,Default,,0,0,0,,And you'll notice that the look on their face\Nis one of just staring off into space.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.10,0:06:32.74,Default,,0,0,0,,There is no hope that life is going to get any better tomorrow.\NAnd so, therefore, hopelessness
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.74,0:06:40.57,Default,,0,0,0,,characterizes the state emotionally.\NAnd in that state, a person is unable to help themself.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.57,0:06:47.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Hopelessness means just that.\NSo a friend of mine was president of the Nassau County Bar Association,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.60,0:06:53.02,Default,,0,0,0,,and he died of starvation\Nall alone in a rooming house.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.02,0:06:58.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Starvation on a combination of alcohol and Librium.\NWhy didn't he call somebody?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.37,0:07:03.40,Default,,0,0,0,,He knew thousands of people.\NHe was very well respected and well loved and well liked.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.40,0:07:08.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Why didn't he just call somebody?\NBecause out of hopelessness, it means just that.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.72,0:07:16.58,Default,,0,0,0,,There being no hope, there, of course, would be no purpose to make a phone call.\NThis is extremely important because when patients come in,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.58,0:07:20.58,Default,,0,0,0,,when people come in in a state of hopelessness,\Ninto the villa,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.58,0:07:22.58,Default,,0,0,0,,into the hospital,\Ninto the office,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.58,0:07:27.58,Default,,0,0,0,,into our groups,\Ninto the influence of our energy field,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.58,0:07:34.00,Default,,0,0,0,,because they cannot help themself,\Nthe only thing you can do is pour energy into them.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.00,0:07:41.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Because the process over on the right hand side is loss of energy,\Nthen all you can do is pour energy into the person.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.26,0:07:48.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Reason and logic has no effect on a person in that state of consciousness.\NSo the mother who has lost her child,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.29,0:07:54.42,Default,,0,0,0,,you know, got a telegram from the State Department,\Nthat your son is missing in action,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.42,0:07:59.42,Default,,0,0,0,,suddenly stops speaking, she sits in her rocking chair,\Nshe stares blankly out the window,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.42,0:08:04.58,Default,,0,0,0,,rocks back and forth and stops eating,\Nand doesn't respond to people anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.58,0:08:12.58,Default,,0,0,0,,And now, when a telegram comes from the State Department that it was a mistake,\Nit was another man with a similar name and they say,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.58,0:08:17.58,Default,,0,0,0,,mother, mother, it was all a mistake.\NYou know, it wasn't really Richard at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.58,0:08:24.02,Default,,0,0,0,,So she just stares blankly out the window and rocks back and forth.\NAnd they say, mother, didn't you hear what we said?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.02,0:08:28.02,Default,,0,0,0,,But you see, the state has already changed.\NYour state of consciousness has changed.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.02,0:08:35.02,Default,,0,0,0,,And in this state, because there is changes in the brain enzymes,\Nso over on the left we're going to have a column,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.02,0:08:43.18,Default,,0,0,0,,we could have a blackboard about 30 feet long,\Nin which we're going to integrate the entire cosmos and all of man's experience.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.18,0:08:50.18,Default,,0,0,0,,But having a blackboard of this length will do it serially.\NSo obviously you see there are brain enzyme changes,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.18,0:08:56.28,Default,,0,0,0,,and at this point,\Nat the very bottom you have actually the release of a death hormone.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.28,0:09:02.02,Default,,0,0,0,,You have the release of a death hormone.\NAbove that, in a state higher than that,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.02,0:09:09.02,Default,,0,0,0,,of course you have the depression of the brain's neurotransmitters,\Nthe so-called catecholamines,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.02,0:09:16.56,Default,,0,0,0,,such as serotonin and norepinephrine.\NThose brain enzymes, which when they become depleted,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.56,0:09:20.56,Default,,0,0,0,,throw a person into depression.\NAnd of course this happens in the addictions,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.56,0:09:25.56,Default,,0,0,0,,where first there is an overstimulation of those neurotransmitters,\Nand then with the withdrawal of the drug,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.56,0:09:30.56,Default,,0,0,0,,especially a drug like cocaine,\Nthere is then a severe depression of the neurotransmitters,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.56,0:09:36.56,Default,,0,0,0,,and therefore drugs that have an up-effect\Nwill throw a person into a depression when you remove them.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.56,0:09:44.90,Default,,0,0,0,,The woman does not respond to the message\Nthat her son was not killed in action,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.90,0:09:49.90,Default,,0,0,0,,because she's no longer capable of that.\NAnd so the only thing we can do for a person
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.90,0:09:54.96,Default,,0,0,0,,in this energy field is to pour energy into them.\NPour energy into them
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.96,0:09:59.96,Default,,0,0,0,,by our presence, by our caring for them,\Nby our prayers for them,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.96,0:10:03.96,Default,,0,0,0,,by the sheer presence of our own physical energy\Nand our caringness,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.96,0:10:12.02,Default,,0,0,0,,because the person is unable to care for themself,\Nin an attempt to get them up to the next higher energy field called grief.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.02,0:10:18.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Grief, which calibrates at 50,\Nhas a lot more energy than apathy at 50.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.02,0:10:23.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Grief at 75 has a lot more energy.\NAnd how is that energy expressed?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.27,0:10:26.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Through emotion.\NSo we know that when the mother
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.27,0:10:31.34,Default,,0,0,0,,rocking back and forth in the rocking chair\Nsuddenly begins to cry,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.34,0:10:35.40,Default,,0,0,0,,we know that she's getting better.\NThere's an expression of emotion,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.40,0:10:42.40,Default,,0,0,0,,and grief has a certain biologic purpose in the universe,\Nso that it summons forth some kind of a biologic response.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.40,0:10:49.94,Default,,0,0,0,,When the infant cries, it summons the mother.\NA couple of months ago, I was sitting on my front porch
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.94,0:10:53.94,Default,,0,0,0,,and I heard this little squeaking sound.\NSqueak, squeak, squeak, squeak.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.94,0:10:57.94,Default,,0,0,0,,And my cat went over to a flower pot,\Nyou know, was very curious about the flower pot,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.94,0:11:01.94,Default,,0,0,0,,and I lifted up the flower pot,\Nand here's this little toad underneath.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.94,0:11:04.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Hop, hop, out.\NHe'd been trapped there.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.94,0:11:07.94,Default,,0,0,0,,So this little toad, you see, in his grief,\Nhis little expression,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.94,0:11:10.94,Default,,0,0,0,,summoned forth a great power from the universe,\Nnamely me,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.94,0:11:14.94,Default,,0,0,0,,to take the flower pot off him\Nwith the help of the kitty.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.94,0:11:18.94,Default,,0,0,0,,So, you see that little squeak,\Nsummoned forth the cat,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.94,0:11:22.94,Default,,0,0,0,,and the cat summoned forth me,\Nand so therefore you see in operation
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.94,0:11:26.94,Default,,0,0,0,,the power, you see the power,\Nbecause we say the energy fields are not personal.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.94,0:11:30.94,Default,,0,0,0,,So what the little toad was expressing\Nwas that energy field, you see,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.94,0:11:35.94,Default,,0,0,0,,and that energy field summoned the two of us.\NSo there is power in grief.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.94,0:11:42.32,Default,,0,0,0,,In ordinary life, we experience grief,\Nin ordinary daily life, as regret.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.32,0:11:45.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Regret.\NSo that grief relates to the past,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.32,0:11:49.77,Default,,0,0,0,,just as fear, the energy field above it,\Nrelates to the future.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.77,0:11:54.77,Default,,0,0,0,,We experience grief in the form of regret,\Nhaving to do with loss,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.77,0:11:59.77,Default,,0,0,0,,the feeling of loss,\Nand it leads eventually into depression.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.77,0:12:04.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Depression leads then, if it gets worse,\Nslips into despondency, into hopelessness,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.77,0:12:10.31,Default,,0,0,0,,and into the bottom of the box.\NWhat's happened in grief is the person, we say,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.31,0:12:14.73,Default,,0,0,0,,has become dispirited.\NDispirited.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.73,0:12:18.73,Default,,0,0,0,,All of these are coming about,\Nall of these are, we say,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.73,0:12:22.73,Default,,0,0,0,,are accompanied by random changes,\Nbut all of them are coming about
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.73,0:12:26.73,Default,,0,0,0,,because everything under the level of courage\Nis based on the illusion
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.73,0:12:32.92,Default,,0,0,0,,that happiness is something outside of yourself.\NIt's something out there.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.92,0:12:39.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Consequently, grief is a reaction\Nthen to that illusion that happiness is out there
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.21,0:12:44.21,Default,,0,0,0,,and that you have lost it somehow in your life\Nthrough that person, that relationship,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.21,0:12:50.21,Default,,0,0,0,,that money, that position, that title,\Nthe loss of your hair,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.21,0:12:56.59,Default,,0,0,0,,your youth, your vigor, whatever,\Nyour potency, your Cadillac.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.59,0:13:02.59,Default,,0,0,0,,All the things that people put their stuff on\Nas being the source of their happiness.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.59,0:13:07.94,Default,,0,0,0,,It's always out there.\NAnd so the loss of out there leads to the feeling of regret,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.94,0:13:15.03,Default,,0,0,0,,loss, depression, and the dispirited state.\NThese lower states, grief and apathy,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.03,0:13:21.19,Default,,0,0,0,,come from the failure to face the energy field above it,\Nwhich is fear.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.19,0:13:25.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Fear, again a reversed energy field,\Ncalibrates at 100.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.19,0:13:29.19,Default,,0,0,0,,So 100 is a lot of energy.\NYou think what you can do with the energy
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.19,0:13:33.26,Default,,0,0,0,,of fear, not with the emotion of fear,\Nbut with the energy of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.26,0:13:38.26,Default,,0,0,0,,You can run like hell with fear.\NYou can establish the whole Maginot Line,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.26,0:13:43.26,Default,,0,0,0,,which the French did\Nin preparing for the onset of the Germans in World War II.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.26,0:13:50.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Fear motivates, obviously, a huge amount of human behavior\Nand sells insurance policies
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.35,0:13:54.35,Default,,0,0,0,,and a good part of our economy,\Nof course, is based on fear and the defenses.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.48,0:13:59.48,Default,,0,0,0,,So there's a lot of energy in fear.\NAnd what we try to teach people to do
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.48,0:14:04.48,Default,,0,0,0,,is how to use the energy of these fields,\Nbut not the emotion itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.48,0:14:09.67,Default,,0,0,0,,How to use the energy constructively\Ncoming out of fear.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.67,0:14:13.67,Default,,0,0,0,,So all these energy fields have their upside\Nand their downside.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.67,0:14:19.67,Default,,0,0,0,,The upside and the downside.\NThe upside of fear is how to use that energy constructively
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.67,0:14:23.67,Default,,0,0,0,,because you can do yourself a great favor\Nif you know what to be afraid of in this world.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.67,0:14:28.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Isn't that so?\NTo be afraid of the addiction, for instance,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.02,0:14:31.63,Default,,0,0,0,,is sensible in as much as it is.\NI'll tell you.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.63,0:14:35.63,Default,,0,0,0,,In ordinary life,\Nwe experience the energy field of fear
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.63,0:14:40.73,Default,,0,0,0,,as worry.\NWorry, anxiety, panic.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.73,0:14:45.73,Default,,0,0,0,,So fear has to do with the future.\NIt has to do with anticipated consequences.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.73,0:14:51.73,Default,,0,0,0,,It has to do with all kinds of projections.\NAnd the process going on over here in consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.73,0:14:56.02,Default,,0,0,0,,is one of deflation.\NSo the animal, when it's afraid,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.02,0:15:00.02,Default,,0,0,0,,shrinks and hides\Nand tries to camouflage itself and be invisible.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.02,0:15:04.02,Default,,0,0,0,,And we all remember that in class,\Nyou know, in second grade.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.02,0:15:08.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Anybody know how much is so-and-so?\NAnd everybody shrinks behind the person in front of them
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.02,0:15:12.02,Default,,0,0,0,,and tries to become invisible.\NSo this is where we like to become invisible
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.02,0:15:16.02,Default,,0,0,0,,and disappear.\NAnd the whole animal kingdom reflects that
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.02,0:15:20.02,Default,,0,0,0,,in its magnificent camouflage\Nin which the insects and the birds and the animals
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.02,0:15:27.88,Default,,0,0,0,,look like tree bark and various things.\NTo become invisible and disappear from attack.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.88,0:15:31.88,Default,,0,0,0,,And that is the basis, of course,\Nof the psychological mechanisms
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.88,0:15:35.88,Default,,0,0,0,,to disappear from the space,\Nto disappear yourself from the space
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.88,0:15:40.91,Default,,0,0,0,,through denial and projection\Nand ways to remove yourself from being there.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.91,0:15:48.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Facing this energy field of fear\Nis what prevents falling into depression and despondency.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.81,0:15:57.29,Default,,0,0,0,,So the way out of depression and despondency\Nfor anyone is to face what is the underlying fear.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.29,0:16:01.29,Default,,0,0,0,,The reason you're depressed\Nis because you're unwilling to face
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.29,0:16:06.45,Default,,0,0,0,,what is the fear underlying the depression.\NFear is much easier to handle
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.45,0:16:10.45,Default,,0,0,0,,once you understand how to handle fear\Nthan is depression.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.45,0:16:15.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Depression really, in a way, can't be handled\Nexcept to look at what was not faced
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.99,0:16:19.99,Default,,0,0,0,,that will pull you out of it.\NThe minute you look at what the fear is
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.99,0:16:21.99,Default,,0,0,0,,underlying the depression,\Ndepression now disappears
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.99,0:16:25.99,Default,,0,0,0,,and instead you feel afraid.\NAnd what is the fear usually?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.99,0:16:29.99,Default,,0,0,0,,It usually takes the form of\NI have lost my happiness.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.99,0:16:35.18,Default,,0,0,0,,The source.\NI have lost the source of my happiness forever.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.18,0:16:39.18,Default,,0,0,0,,You'll see that under depression\Nis the thought, the fantasy,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.18,0:16:44.34,Default,,0,0,0,,the idea, and the emotion.\NSo the woman is saying,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.34,0:16:49.34,Default,,0,0,0,,without my son, life is now meaningless to me.\NHe was my life.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.34,0:16:53.40,Default,,0,0,0,,I based my life around my son\Nand what he was in the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.40,0:16:57.40,Default,,0,0,0,,And now my life has no meaning.\NSo I have lost the source of meaning
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.40,0:17:01.40,Default,,0,0,0,,and happiness in my life.\NSo depression then comes from
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.40,0:17:04.40,Default,,0,0,0,,what is the fear?\NThe fear almost always takes the form
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.40,0:17:09.04,Default,,0,0,0,,I have lost the source of my happiness.\NHow is fear handled?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.04,0:17:14.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, we teach people how to handle fear.\NIt's a very simple thing to handle.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.04,0:17:20.30,Default,,0,0,0,,It's surprisingly one of the easiest things to learn.\NHandling fear then is merely
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.30,0:17:26.30,Default,,0,0,0,,handling the fear of the fear.\NAnd the way you handle fear is by disassembling it.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.30,0:17:30.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Taking the fear away from the fear.\NOnce you're no longer afraid of fear,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.30,0:17:33.36,Default,,0,0,0,,it's really a nothing.\NWhen you disassemble it
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.36,0:17:37.36,Default,,0,0,0,,and take it down to what it is,\Nyou know, fear is
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.36,0:17:41.36,Default,,0,0,0,,a feeling of dryness in the mouth,\Nmaybe palpitations,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.36,0:17:45.42,Default,,0,0,0,,maybe some weakness in the legs,\Nbutterflies in the stomach,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.42,0:17:49.42,Default,,0,0,0,,gastrointestinal discomfort,\Nwhatever.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.42,0:17:53.42,Default,,0,0,0,,If you ask yourself,\Nyou know, could I handle that?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.42,0:17:57.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Could I let go resisting that?\NSo what you do is you let go resisting
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.46,0:18:00.46,Default,,0,0,0,,what you're actually experiencing\Nand stop labeling it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.46,0:18:03.46,Default,,0,0,0,,You stop giving it any attention\Nto what the thoughts are
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.46,0:18:05.46,Default,,0,0,0,,because what kind of thoughts\Ndo you think fear is going to put out?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.46,0:18:09.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Actually, it's going to put out your thoughts.\NSo instead, what you concentrate on
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.46,0:18:13.46,Default,,0,0,0,,is the sensations running through your body\Nand you're asking yourself,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.46,0:18:17.71,Default,,0,0,0,,could you let go resisting them?\NAnd you just keep letting go resisting them
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.71,0:18:22.93,Default,,0,0,0,,and you find that there's nothing to it.\NI let fear run one time for two weeks solid
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.93,0:18:27.93,Default,,0,0,0,,and when it left, I missed it.\NI mean, it's like my pal by now.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.93,0:18:31.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Just those sensations running through you.\NAnd after the first few minutes
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.93,0:18:35.93,Default,,0,0,0,,or after the first hour or so,\Nif you have really a big one that you're handling,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.93,0:18:39.25,Default,,0,0,0,,letting run out,\Nyou'll find that you go right on functioning
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.25,0:18:43.25,Default,,0,0,0,,and that the fearful feelings running through your body\Nare nothing at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.25,0:18:47.25,Default,,0,0,0,,You feel fear running through you\Nas a physical experience
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.25,0:18:51.25,Default,,0,0,0,,which is quite tolerable\Nand it's really nothing at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.25,0:18:55.25,Default,,0,0,0,,It's much easier to handle, frankly, than a headache.\NIt's easier to handle with nausea.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.25,0:18:59.25,Default,,0,0,0,,It's easier to handle with a broken toe.\NI mean, all the things that you've handled in your life,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.25,0:19:02.25,Default,,0,0,0,,fear is really nothing.\NSo when you lose your fear of fear
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.25,0:19:08.25,Default,,0,0,0,,and are willing to handle fear as it comes up,\Nthen the world in a way can really no longer control you
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.25,0:19:12.25,Default,,0,0,0,,because it's fear, isn't it,\Nthat really runs you
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.25,0:19:17.25,Default,,0,0,0,,and that you're at the effect of so much in this world.\NSo losing your fear of fear
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.25,0:19:22.25,Default,,0,0,0,,and just realizing what it is\Nthat is really a nothing to handle experientially.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.25,0:19:31.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes?\NYes, because the thoughts are an elaboration
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.85,0:19:37.85,Default,,0,0,0,,and there's no truth in them.\NAnd the only thing that you're really experiencing
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.85,0:19:42.85,Default,,0,0,0,,and you force the person to...\NIt's how you do it with physical symptoms as well
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.85,0:19:47.85,Default,,0,0,0,,and that's part of self-healing.\NAnd I've done some tapes and things on self-healing
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.85,0:19:53.85,Default,,0,0,0,,and how I healed many things within myself\Nwas using that technique of stop labeling it,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.85,0:19:56.85,Default,,0,0,0,,stop calling it anything\Nand go into radical truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.85,0:20:01.85,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, radically, what is it you're experiencing?\NRadically speaking, what is it you're experiencing?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.85,0:20:04.85,Default,,0,0,0,,You're not experiencing fear.\NAny more than you can experience
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.85,0:20:07.85,Default,,0,0,0,,asthma or allergies or hay fever.\NThose are all concepts.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.85,0:20:10.85,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't experience hay fever.\NYou can't experience sinus trouble.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.85,0:20:15.52,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't experience any of those things.\NYou can't experience an ulcer.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.52,0:20:17.52,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, radically speaking,\Nwhat is it you're experiencing?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.52,0:20:22.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, you're experiencing a stuffy nose.\NEven stuffiness you're not experiencing
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.52,0:20:25.52,Default,,0,0,0,,any more than with an ulcer.\NThe person says,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.52,0:20:28.52,Default,,0,0,0,,you know, I'm feeling an ulcer.\NYou're not feeling an ulcer.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.52,0:20:32.52,Default,,0,0,0,,What is it you're actually feeling?\NYou're feeling a sensation.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.52,0:20:36.52,Default,,0,0,0,,And of course, all of us who do it,\Nwe just learned that the first day, didn't we,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.52,0:20:39.52,Default,,0,0,0,,when we couldn't go to the bathroom.\NYou had to cancel,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.52,0:20:42.52,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't go to the bathroom,\Nbecause that's a panicky thought.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.52,0:20:46.52,Default,,0,0,0,,And instead, you had to concentrate\Non the fact that what are you radically experiencing?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.52,0:20:51.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, you're experiencing a pressure in the lower abdomen.\NWell, can you handle a little pressure in the lower abdomen?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.52,0:20:53.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, you can handle that.\NBut you cannot handle a thought,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.52,0:20:57.97,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't go to the bathroom,\Nbecause that's a panicsville.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.97,0:21:02.97,Default,,0,0,0,,So, the same, whether you can't handle asthma,\Nyou can't handle any of these labels,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.97,0:21:05.97,Default,,0,0,0,,but what you can handle\Nis the sensation,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.97,0:21:10.35,Default,,0,0,0,,and let go resisting the sensation.\NIn my own personal experience of that,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.35,0:21:15.35,Default,,0,0,0,,all of these physical things will disappear\Nas you keep letting go resisting
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.35,0:21:20.35,Default,,0,0,0,,the physicality of the sensation of it,\Nand let go of the thoughts that go with it.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.35,0:21:23.58,Default,,0,0,0,,So fear,\Nand we teach people how to handle fear,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.58,0:21:27.58,Default,,0,0,0,,is really a nothing.\NAnd of course, one of the first benefits you get out of it,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.58,0:21:32.58,Default,,0,0,0,,out of the willingness to handle the fear,\Nis the letting go of the depression.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.58,0:21:37.58,Default,,0,0,0,,You come out of depression instantly,\Nout of hopelessness instantly,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.58,0:21:42.70,Default,,0,0,0,,the instant you're willing to handle the fear.\NBut people are not willing to handle fear
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.70,0:21:47.70,Default,,0,0,0,,unless they feel there's a safe way to hold that fear,\Nand therefore we're going to be talking about
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.70,0:21:53.70,Default,,0,0,0,,how to hold some of these experiences.\NSee, the context out of which you're holding that fear
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.70,0:21:58.70,Default,,0,0,0,,is now that you are bigger than the fear.\NYou are the healer of that fear.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.70,0:22:03.70,Default,,0,0,0,,You are the one that is holding the field\Nout of which that fear is now being held.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.70,0:22:06.70,Default,,0,0,0,,So you're not at the effect of it.\NSee, you've summoned it.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.70,0:22:10.90,Default,,0,0,0,,You are the master now, see?\NIt's the difference between whether a dog is barking
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.90,0:22:13.90,Default,,0,0,0,,against your will,\Nor whether you invite the dog to bark.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:13.90,0:22:16.93,Default,,0,0,0,,You see?\NAre you saying that the best way to begin,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:16.93,0:22:27.03,Default,,0,0,0,,from my point of view...\NYou move into the physical,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:27.03,0:22:31.03,Default,,0,0,0,,because the mind in panic\Nis like a computer going wild.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.03,0:22:34.03,Default,,0,0,0,,And when you push fear button,\Nit has enough fear programs
Dialogue: 0,0:22:34.03,0:22:38.03,Default,,0,0,0,,that you could think nothing but fear thoughts\Nthe rest of your time on the planet,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:38.03,0:22:40.03,Default,,0,0,0,,and it would never run out.\NIn fact, those fear thoughts
Dialogue: 0,0:22:40.03,0:22:43.03,Default,,0,0,0,,would have engendered\Nwhole new banks of fear thoughts.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:43.03,0:22:46.03,Default,,0,0,0,,The collective consciousness,\Nthe number of fear thoughts
Dialogue: 0,0:22:46.03,0:22:50.03,Default,,0,0,0,,in the collective consciousness\Nis probably infinite, you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:50.03,0:22:52.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Self-perpetuating.\NEvery fearful thought
Dialogue: 0,0:22:52.03,0:22:58.03,Default,,0,0,0,,creates a whole new bank of...\NSo, trying to handle the fear thoughts,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:58.03,0:23:01.03,Default,,0,0,0,,in my experience,\Nis not too successful.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:01.03,0:23:05.03,Default,,0,0,0,,If you handle the actual sensation,\Nfor instance,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:05.03,0:23:08.03,Default,,0,0,0,,you'll come out of depression.\NThe instant you come out of depression,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:08.03,0:23:12.03,Default,,0,0,0,,what you're facing is\Nwhat you thought was the source of your happiness
Dialogue: 0,0:23:12.03,0:23:15.03,Default,,0,0,0,,that you think you have lost.\NAnd so, you're now facing...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:15.03,0:23:19.03,Default,,0,0,0,,You're getting right down to the truth.\NYou're getting much closer to the truth,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.03,0:23:22.54,Default,,0,0,0,,which, of course, has a powerful effect.\NIn the addictions,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:22.54,0:23:26.54,Default,,0,0,0,,we try to get people to do that.\NYou see, they come in in apathy.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.54,0:23:28.54,Default,,0,0,0,,My situation is hopeless.\NMy case is hopeless.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:28.54,0:23:32.54,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, my case is different.\NAnd AA is fine for you folks.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.54,0:23:36.54,Default,,0,0,0,,And NA is fine for you folks.\NAnd OA is fine for you folks.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:36.54,0:23:39.54,Default,,0,0,0,,All that stuff is okay for you.\NMy case is different.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:39.54,0:23:41.54,Default,,0,0,0,,And how is it different?\NMy case is hopeless.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:41.54,0:23:46.99,Default,,0,0,0,,My case is hopeless.\NTo move them up out of hopelessness into grief.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:46.99,0:23:50.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Because when you begin to see the cost of,\Nnot only addiction,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:50.99,0:23:54.99,Default,,0,0,0,,but any physical illness\Nor any problem in your life,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:54.99,0:23:58.06,Default,,0,0,0,,the next reaction you get is grief.\NBecause you see the loss.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:58.06,0:24:02.06,Default,,0,0,0,,You see the cost.\NBecause grief is really about cost.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:02.06,0:24:05.06,Default,,0,0,0,,You see what the cost has been.\NThe price.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:05.06,0:24:08.06,Default,,0,0,0,,And you see what you've sold out\Nand what you've let go of.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.06,0:24:13.06,Default,,0,0,0,,And so therefore you move up\Ninto a regret and a grief.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:13.06,0:24:17.06,Default,,0,0,0,,And in the addictive field,\Npeople go into regret and grief
Dialogue: 0,0:24:17.06,0:24:21.06,Default,,0,0,0,,over the loss that has occurred already\Nin their life about addiction.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:21.06,0:24:25.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Then they move up to fear\Nbecause grief having handled the past.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:25.41,0:24:29.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Fear now, they extrapolate\Nwhat has happened in the past.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:29.41,0:24:31.41,Default,,0,0,0,,And unless you're somewhat retarded,\Nyou begin to realize
Dialogue: 0,0:24:31.41,0:24:34.41,Default,,0,0,0,,that this is a progressive illness\Nand that the losses of the past
Dialogue: 0,0:24:34.41,0:24:37.41,Default,,0,0,0,,are nothing compared to\Nwhat they are going to be in the future.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:37.41,0:24:41.41,Default,,0,0,0,,So far, you know,\Nyou've lost a part of your stomach.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:41.41,0:24:43.41,Default,,0,0,0,,If you keep on drinking,\Nyou will lose your entire stomach.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:43.41,0:24:48.41,Default,,0,0,0,,That becomes rather clear to people.\NAnd so therefore they go into fear.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:48.41,0:24:53.95,Default,,0,0,0,,You move people up from fear\Ninto wanting something better for themselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:53.95,0:24:57.95,Default,,0,0,0,,To move them to the next level,\Nthat of desire.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:57.95,0:25:02.14,Default,,0,0,0,,The energy level of desire,\Nwhich calibrates at 125,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:02.14,0:25:04.14,Default,,0,0,0,,has a lot of power in it.\NIt's obvious to all of us
Dialogue: 0,0:25:04.14,0:25:07.14,Default,,0,0,0,,that desire runs all of Madison Avenue,\Nthe whole marketing,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:07.14,0:25:10.14,Default,,0,0,0,,the whole marketing schemes\Nof the whole United States,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:10.14,0:25:15.14,Default,,0,0,0,,the basis of the economy.\NAnd desire and the wanting of something
Dialogue: 0,0:25:15.14,0:25:25.33,Default,,0,0,0,,can drive your entire lifetime.\NThere was a question in the back.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:25.33,0:25:27.33,Default,,0,0,0,,The technique of it\NI won't go into today
Dialogue: 0,0:25:27.33,0:25:30.33,Default,,0,0,0,,because it is all part of research\Nand consciousness,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:30.33,0:25:33.33,Default,,0,0,0,,but I'll tell you a couple of easy ways\Nand we will do one of them in class.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:33.33,0:25:39.33,Default,,0,0,0,,We ourselves will calibrate the truth\Nof what we're talking about today in class.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:39.33,0:25:43.33,Default,,0,0,0,,And we'll use a very simple method\Nthat anybody can use.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:43.33,0:25:45.33,Default,,0,0,0,,There are even faster,\Nsimpler ways, of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:45.33,0:25:49.33,Default,,0,0,0,,But we ourselves will test out the truth\Nof everything said today.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:49.33,0:25:52.33,Default,,0,0,0,,And I always say,\Nnever believe anything a speaker says
Dialogue: 0,0:25:52.33,0:25:58.42,Default,,0,0,0,,unless you have yourself\Ninvestigated their integrity,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:58.42,0:26:00.42,Default,,0,0,0,,their energy,\Ntheir reversity,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:00.42,0:26:03.42,Default,,0,0,0,,and where they're at.\NSo everything that we say today,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:03.42,0:26:06.42,Default,,0,0,0,,we will test out.\NAnd during the bill of lectures,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:06.42,0:26:08.42,Default,,0,0,0,,we literally do that,\Nthe whole class.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:08.42,0:26:13.42,Default,,0,0,0,,We test out the various propositions\Nthat we have presented during these talks
Dialogue: 0,0:26:13.42,0:26:17.42,Default,,0,0,0,,and prove whether they're so or not so,\Nespecially the most critical ones
Dialogue: 0,0:26:17.42,0:26:21.42,Default,,0,0,0,,because today we'll be talking about\Nwhat people are actually addicted to,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:21.42,0:26:27.97,Default,,0,0,0,,which is something that escapes the world thus far.\NSo fear, then, is a very useful thing
Dialogue: 0,0:26:27.97,0:26:31.97,Default,,0,0,0,,if you use out of the energy of fear,\Nthe fear of the addiction,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:31.97,0:26:35.97,Default,,0,0,0,,driving you into wanting this,\Nsomething better for yourself,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:35.97,0:26:40.97,Default,,0,0,0,,to desire something better for yourself.\NSo desire at 125,000,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:40.97,0:26:43.97,Default,,0,0,0,,that's a lot of power.\NAnd we experience it in ordinary life
Dialogue: 0,0:26:43.97,0:26:46.97,Default,,0,0,0,,as wanting this,\Nyou know, craving this,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:46.97,0:26:49.97,Default,,0,0,0,,the lust,\Nlust in its generic widest meaning.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:49.97,0:26:54.97,Default,,0,0,0,,And in the addictions,\Nthey eventually become obsession and compulsions.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:54.97,0:26:58.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Obsessions and compulsions,\Nin which the person is willing to sacrifice
Dialogue: 0,0:26:58.97,0:27:03.97,Default,,0,0,0,,and sell out everything\Nin the name of that obsession and compulsion,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:03.97,0:27:07.97,Default,,0,0,0,,including life itself,\Nall that life entails.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:07.97,0:27:10.97,Default,,0,0,0,,And in the end,\Nthe addiction will ask for your body,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:10.97,0:27:12.97,Default,,0,0,0,,and in the end,\Nyou will give it your body.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:12.97,0:27:16.97,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, the fact that even the physical body\Nis going to go in the end,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:16.97,0:27:19.97,Default,,0,0,0,,you will say,\Nwell, if it goes, it goes, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:19.97,0:27:23.97,Default,,0,0,0,,piecemeal or in toto,\Nbecause by then everything else is gone
Dialogue: 0,0:27:23.97,0:27:27.97,Default,,0,0,0,,and the only thing you've got left is the body,\Nand so that's going to go too.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:27.97,0:27:30.97,Default,,0,0,0,,So the person in the end\Nis willing then to give up the body.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:30.97,0:27:33.97,Default,,0,0,0,,So we know you can't scare people\Nout of the addictions.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:33.97,0:27:36.97,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't scare people saying,\Nif you keep doing this,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:36.97,0:27:39.97,Default,,0,0,0,,you're going to do that.\NIt doesn't mean anything to the person,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:39.97,0:27:43.97,Default,,0,0,0,,because they are quite willing to do that.\NAt a certain level of consciousness,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:43.97,0:27:48.58,Default,,0,0,0,,they are willing to do everything\Nto maintain that which they are seeking.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:48.58,0:27:53.58,Default,,0,0,0,,The energy field of desire then,\Nto begin to want something better for yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:53.58,0:27:57.58,Default,,0,0,0,,So out of hopelessness,\Nto move the person into grief,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:57.58,0:28:01.58,Default,,0,0,0,,and grief to face the fear,\Nthe fear I will never be happy again,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:01.58,0:28:05.58,Default,,0,0,0,,because in the addictions, obviously,\Nthe source of your happiness is out here.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:05.58,0:28:09.58,Default,,0,0,0,,So to cut a person off from the addiction,\Nyou then see why they go into grief,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:09.58,0:28:12.58,Default,,0,0,0,,because they have just lost\Nthe source of their happiness.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:12.58,0:28:14.58,Default,,0,0,0,,To move up to fear,\Nto move up to desire,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:14.58,0:28:19.58,Default,,0,0,0,,for wanting something to crave,\Nto really want something
Dialogue: 0,0:28:19.58,0:28:23.93,Default,,0,0,0,,that is better for yourself,\Nand move out of the grief and the fear,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:23.93,0:28:28.02,Default,,0,0,0,,and move up to anger.\NIf you can move a person up to anger,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:28.02,0:28:32.02,Default,,0,0,0,,anger over what?\NAnger over being victim.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:32.02,0:28:36.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Anger over being victim.\NAnger over being powerless.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:36.02,0:28:42.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Anger over what the cost has been.\NAnger at how you've had to sell yourself out
Dialogue: 0,0:28:42.02,0:28:46.02,Default,,0,0,0,,in order to survive.\NAnger at the sheer cost of survival,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:46.02,0:28:50.02,Default,,0,0,0,,the sheer cost that you've had to pay\Nin order to maintain this.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:50.02,0:28:55.41,Default,,0,0,0,,So we experience anger in ordinary life\Nas resentment, you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:55.41,0:28:59.41,Default,,0,0,0,,In daily life, it's resentment,\Nand of course that intensifies
Dialogue: 0,0:28:59.41,0:29:04.41,Default,,0,0,0,,to hatred and grudges,\Neventually killing and war.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:04.41,0:29:08.76,Default,,0,0,0,,The thing about desire,\Nthe situation with desire,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:08.76,0:29:12.76,Default,,0,0,0,,the desire that addiction itself,\Nyou see the process in consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:29:12.76,0:29:17.98,Default,,0,0,0,,is one of entrapment.\NThe person is trapped by the addiction.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:17.98,0:29:21.98,Default,,0,0,0,,They're at the effect of it.\NSo if Madison Avenue can program you
Dialogue: 0,0:29:21.98,0:29:25.98,Default,,0,0,0,,with a certain want,\Na certain desire,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:25.98,0:29:29.98,Default,,0,0,0,,then you are run by that,\Nand you then will put forth
Dialogue: 0,0:29:29.98,0:29:33.98,Default,,0,0,0,,your money, time, energy, and effort\Nto get that which you want,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:33.98,0:29:37.98,Default,,0,0,0,,which is usually based on\Nyou won't have what other people have,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:37.98,0:29:40.98,Default,,0,0,0,,or they'll think you have B.O.,\Nor they won't love you,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:40.98,0:29:43.98,Default,,0,0,0,,or your hair won't swirl in the wind\Nand make men go crazy,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:43.98,0:29:48.98,Default,,0,0,0,,or whatever the picture program\Nhas gone into your unconscious.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:48.98,0:29:51.98,Default,,0,0,0,,To be at the effect of that,\Nyou have to have that Cadillac
Dialogue: 0,0:29:51.98,0:29:55.98,Default,,0,0,0,,in order to be happy,\Notherwise people will not respect you, etc.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:55.98,0:29:58.98,Default,,0,0,0,,So whatever you're entrapped by then\Nruns you.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:58.98,0:30:02.98,Default,,0,0,0,,So from this level then,\Nthe person is obviously run by that.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:02.98,0:30:05.98,Default,,0,0,0,,And so we get people to see that,\Nand a lot of times they will go
Dialogue: 0,0:30:05.98,0:30:10.02,Default,,0,0,0,,directly right into anger.\NWhat's the good of anger is that
Dialogue: 0,0:30:10.02,0:30:14.02,Default,,0,0,0,,it has an energy fuel of 150.\NThe energy of anger,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:14.02,0:30:17.02,Default,,0,0,0,,not the emotion of it,\Nwhich leads to destruction,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:17.02,0:30:21.02,Default,,0,0,0,,destructive action,\Nbut the energy of the anger
Dialogue: 0,0:30:21.02,0:30:26.08,Default,,0,0,0,,can now be used for constructive action.\NSo that anger over the cost,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:26.08,0:30:30.08,Default,,0,0,0,,over what has been,\Nand move the person up to pride.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:30.08,0:30:35.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Pride at 175 is a lot of energy.\NIt's enough to run the entire
Dialogue: 0,0:30:35.53,0:30:40.94,Default,,0,0,0,,United States Marine Corps.\NPride runs the whole clothing industry,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:40.94,0:30:43.94,Default,,0,0,0,,the cosmetics industry.\NThe pride in one's appearance
Dialogue: 0,0:30:43.94,0:30:49.30,Default,,0,0,0,,and leads you to getting all kinds of degrees\Nand what pride does with us.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:49.30,0:30:52.30,Default,,0,0,0,,I think it's some of the greatest things\NI've done out of pride,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:52.30,0:30:55.30,Default,,0,0,0,,especially in adolescence.\NI mean, it's really something.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:55.30,0:30:58.30,Default,,0,0,0,,What a girl might think about something,\Nand then what it led to,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:58.30,0:31:01.30,Default,,0,0,0,,just to erase that from your collar\Nbecause she might have seen that.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:01.30,0:31:03.30,Default,,0,0,0,,And of course all night\Nyou never even took your coat off,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:03.30,0:31:06.30,Default,,0,0,0,,so she never would have seen it anyway.\NBut the pride,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:06.30,0:31:09.30,Default,,0,0,0,,the energy then of it,\Nis enormous.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:09.30,0:31:13.30,Default,,0,0,0,,If it's used constructively,\Nit's not a great place to hang out in.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:13.30,0:31:19.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Pride is not a great place to hang out in\Nbecause of the defensive nature,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:19.30,0:31:23.30,Default,,0,0,0,,because the process going on in consciousness\Nis really one of inflation.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:23.30,0:31:26.55,Default,,0,0,0,,And the downside of pride,\Nyou see the upside of pride
Dialogue: 0,0:31:26.55,0:31:29.55,Default,,0,0,0,,is to begin to move into self-care,\Nto care about yourself,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:29.55,0:31:33.55,Default,,0,0,0,,and to do something about that,\Nto use that energy of anger
Dialogue: 0,0:31:33.55,0:31:36.55,Default,,0,0,0,,now in a constructive way.\NThe downside of pride,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:36.55,0:31:39.55,Default,,0,0,0,,and of a great importance to pride,\Nto us,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:39.55,0:31:41.55,Default,,0,0,0,,in all fields,\Nbut especially addiction,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:41.55,0:31:43.55,Default,,0,0,0,,is denial.\NSee?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:43.55,0:31:47.55,Default,,0,0,0,,The downside of pride is denial,\Nand in its other forms,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:47.55,0:31:51.55,Default,,0,0,0,,contempt,\Nand the defensiveness that goes with that.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:51.55,0:31:54.62,Default,,0,0,0,,So that denial kills a lot of people\Nin the addictions.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:54.62,0:31:57.62,Default,,0,0,0,,How does it kill them?\NIt kills them,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:57.62,0:32:00.62,Default,,0,0,0,,it happened in my own family,\Nin several of my family members,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:00.62,0:32:04.62,Default,,0,0,0,,closest nuclear family in fact,\Nwhere people would go to a meeting and say,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:04.62,0:32:07.62,Default,,0,0,0,,well those people need that.\NGo to an AA meeting,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:07.62,0:32:09.62,Default,,0,0,0,,they say,\Nwell,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:09.62,0:32:11.62,Default,,0,0,0,,they need that.\NThose people.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:11.62,0:32:14.62,Default,,0,0,0,,And it's usually said,\Nwith sort of looking down the nose,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:14.62,0:32:16.62,Default,,0,0,0,,contemptuous,\Nthat those worms there,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:16.62,0:32:19.62,Default,,0,0,0,,they need that.\NAnd a lot of people in our society
Dialogue: 0,0:32:19.62,0:32:23.62,Default,,0,0,0,,who don't understand self-help groups\Nor spiritually based self-healing
Dialogue: 0,0:32:23.62,0:32:28.62,Default,,0,0,0,,still have that attitude.\NOh, you still need those meetings?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:28.62,0:32:31.62,Default,,0,0,0,,But because you understand what it's all about,\Nyou laugh at it
Dialogue: 0,0:32:31.62,0:32:36.62,Default,,0,0,0,,because you realize that they don't really get it,\Nbut they're projecting this within them.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:36.62,0:32:39.62,Default,,0,0,0,,This within themselves upon that,\Nyou see,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:39.62,0:32:43.62,Default,,0,0,0,,and that's what they see there.\NSo the whole problem with pride is defensiveness,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:43.62,0:32:48.62,Default,,0,0,0,,to be defensive.\NYou know that pride is useful then as a transition.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:48.62,0:32:54.74,Default,,0,0,0,,And even the Marine Corps appeals to pride,\Nbut what they really move you up into is courage.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:54.74,0:33:01.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Because prideful people are hard to handle.\NSo pride is useful as a transition.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:01.10,0:33:05.10,Default,,0,0,0,,The difficulty is that the person's\Nunconsciousness is inflated.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:05.10,0:33:08.10,Default,,0,0,0,,So we say the person\Nis too big for their boots,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:08.10,0:33:14.96,Default,,0,0,0,,you know, that they have a swelled head.\NThe inflation is,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:14.96,0:33:17.96,Default,,0,0,0,,and you see coming,\Nthe state right below that, anger,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:17.96,0:33:21.96,Default,,0,0,0,,is one of expansion.\NBut this is one of inflation.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:21.96,0:33:28.96,Default,,0,0,0,,In anger, the process is one to become expanded.\NSo the animal that is in anger,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:28.96,0:33:33.96,Default,,0,0,0,,its hair stands on end and its tail swells\Nand it looks fierce and it expands itself
Dialogue: 0,0:33:33.96,0:33:37.96,Default,,0,0,0,,to make itself a formidable opponent.\NSo the person in anger,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:37.96,0:33:42.96,Default,,0,0,0,,their veins swell out and they swell out\Nand take up a lot of energy space
Dialogue: 0,0:33:42.96,0:33:45.96,Default,,0,0,0,,to try and impose on you and scare you.\NBoo.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:45.96,0:33:50.96,Default,,0,0,0,,The anger then is an expanded state.\NBut pride is an inflated state,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:50.96,0:33:54.96,Default,,0,0,0,,which is somewhat beyond that\Nand has its own characteristics,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:54.96,0:33:59.96,Default,,0,0,0,,particularly that of denial.\NSo we hear out of that coming contempt.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:59.96,0:34:04.96,Default,,0,0,0,,And the contempt for that,\Nexactly what a person needs,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:04.96,0:34:09.96,Default,,0,0,0,,exactly what the person needs\Nis exactly what they have the contempt for
Dialogue: 0,0:34:09.96,0:34:12.96,Default,,0,0,0,,because they're unable to handle that\Nbecause out of pridefulness,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:12.96,0:34:18.96,Default,,0,0,0,,there is the inability to accept one's limitations\Nand therefore they have to be projected
Dialogue: 0,0:34:18.96,0:34:24.28,Default,,0,0,0,,and ridiculed in others.\NSo we try to move people in the addictions
Dialogue: 0,0:34:24.28,0:34:29.28,Default,,0,0,0,,through pride to use the upside of pride\Nto move into constructive action
Dialogue: 0,0:34:29.28,0:34:33.28,Default,,0,0,0,,and really to move the people up\Ninto the level of courage.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:33.28,0:34:36.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Courage is a critical element\Nto a level.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:36.66,0:34:41.86,Default,,0,0,0,,First of all, we see when we calibrate it\Nthat the energy field has jumped to 200.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:41.86,0:34:45.86,Default,,0,0,0,,200 is a lot of power.\NAn energy field of 200 is enough
Dialogue: 0,0:34:45.86,0:34:49.86,Default,,0,0,0,,to settle the United States of America\Nand settle the West,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:49.86,0:34:52.86,Default,,0,0,0,,to create all the industries,\Nto create all the empires,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:52.86,0:34:56.86,Default,,0,0,0,,to energize all of science.\NCuriosity plus courage is enough
Dialogue: 0,0:34:56.86,0:34:59.86,Default,,0,0,0,,to handle the whole thing.\NSo it's an enormous energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:59.86,0:35:01.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Why does it have so much energy?\NIt has that much energy
Dialogue: 0,0:35:01.86,0:35:05.86,Default,,0,0,0,,because you'll see by the arrows,\Nwhereas these energy fields
Dialogue: 0,0:35:05.86,0:35:10.86,Default,,0,0,0,,were all reversed to the left,\Nthe needle now goes to the middle.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:10.86,0:35:14.86,Default,,0,0,0,,So in the level of courage then,\Nthe energy field has shifted
Dialogue: 0,0:35:14.86,0:35:22.17,Default,,0,0,0,,from destructive to neutral.\NThe energy field is like an antenna.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:22.17,0:35:26.17,Default,,0,0,0,,So you can picture it\Nbecause all things in the universe
Dialogue: 0,0:35:26.17,0:35:30.42,Default,,0,0,0,,give off a vibration, an energy,\Nat a certain frequency,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:30.42,0:35:34.55,Default,,0,0,0,,which is unique to that individual.\NEverything in the universe
Dialogue: 0,0:35:34.55,0:35:38.55,Default,,0,0,0,,gives off an energy and a vibration.\NAnd the track of that energy
Dialogue: 0,0:35:38.55,0:35:46.22,Default,,0,0,0,,and that vibration is there forever.\NThe energy field here is like an antenna,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:46.22,0:35:51.22,Default,,0,0,0,,so that here it's like the antenna\Nis set to negative.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:51.22,0:35:55.22,Default,,0,0,0,,This is like a negative antenna.\NThe negative antenna pulls to it
Dialogue: 0,0:35:55.22,0:36:00.22,Default,,0,0,0,,all that is destructive from the universe.\NAnd so we see at the bottom
Dialogue: 0,0:36:00.22,0:36:03.29,Default,,0,0,0,,the process is one of destruction.\NAt the very bottom,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:03.29,0:36:08.99,Default,,0,0,0,,destruction has finally succeeded.\NThis is an impersonal effect
Dialogue: 0,0:36:08.99,0:36:12.15,Default,,0,0,0,,of the energy field.\NThe person,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:12.15,0:36:17.22,Default,,0,0,0,,electively by his intention,\Nsets what the energy field is.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:17.22,0:36:21.22,Default,,0,0,0,,But then the energy field itself\Nbecomes impersonal.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:21.22,0:36:25.22,Default,,0,0,0,,What happens is you see a sudden\Nsevere reversal of the energy field.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:25.22,0:36:29.22,Default,,0,0,0,,And now when you come back a year later,\Na year later,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:29.22,0:36:32.22,Default,,0,0,0,,and you look at the barn,\Nor let's say you take aerial photographs,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:32.22,0:36:36.22,Default,,0,0,0,,and you come back a year later,\Nyou will see from the aerial photograph
Dialogue: 0,0:36:36.22,0:36:41.31,Default,,0,0,0,,that the foliage in that canyon has changed.\NWhen you visit the barn,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:41.31,0:36:46.31,Default,,0,0,0,,you will see that there are now holes in the roof,\Nand there are now packrats living there,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:46.31,0:36:50.31,Default,,0,0,0,,and there are cockroaches there,\Nand all that is negative
Dialogue: 0,0:36:50.31,0:36:54.31,Default,,0,0,0,,seems to be pulled into this barn,\Nand a quarter of it has fallen down,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:54.31,0:36:57.31,Default,,0,0,0,,and teenagers have kicked the slats out\Nand broken the windows,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:57.31,0:37:00.31,Default,,0,0,0,,and you wonder what happened.\NI mean, I saw it happen to a little cottage
Dialogue: 0,0:37:00.31,0:37:05.31,Default,,0,0,0,,across the creek from where I live,\Nin a beautiful, happy little thing,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:05.31,0:37:08.31,Default,,0,0,0,,through abandonment,\Nand for one thing or another,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:08.31,0:37:12.31,Default,,0,0,0,,its energy got reversed,\Nand now teenagers were like pulled,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:12.31,0:37:15.31,Default,,0,0,0,,you know, like rats and things,\Nand they kicked all the sides in,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:15.31,0:37:17.31,Default,,0,0,0,,and they kicked the roof in,\Nand they kicked the walls in,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:17.31,0:37:20.31,Default,,0,0,0,,and they kicked the windows out,\Nand they kicked the doors in,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:20.31,0:37:24.31,Default,,0,0,0,,and each time I would visit it,\Nsome more things had been kicked.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:24.31,0:37:28.31,Default,,0,0,0,,So once the thing reverses, you see,\Nit pulls further destruction to it.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:28.31,0:37:33.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Hmm.\NThe reason to say that is to get the feeling
Dialogue: 0,0:37:33.56,0:37:37.56,Default,,0,0,0,,of impersonality.\NIt is the energy field now
Dialogue: 0,0:37:37.56,0:37:40.56,Default,,0,0,0,,which pulls that destructive.\NSo the antenna then,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:40.56,0:37:44.56,Default,,0,0,0,,if it's tuned to negative,\Nif it's tuned to reverse,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:44.56,0:37:48.56,Default,,0,0,0,,then pulls into the person's life\Nall that is destructive,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:48.56,0:37:55.72,Default,,0,0,0,,so that the person below this level then\Nis experiencing that reversity,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:55.72,0:38:00.72,Default,,0,0,0,,that negativity in the form\Nof all kinds of adversity.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:00.72,0:38:04.72,Default,,0,0,0,,So it can be a DWI,\Nit can be parking ticket starts out mild,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:04.72,0:38:06.72,Default,,0,0,0,,parking tickets,\Nand then it gets a little worse,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:06.72,0:38:10.72,Default,,0,0,0,,DWIs, and then bankruptcies,\Nand you lost your credit rating,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:10.72,0:38:13.72,Default,,0,0,0,,and the next thing you know,\Nyou find yourself in the county jail,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:13.72,0:38:17.72,Default,,0,0,0,,and your relationships go to hell,\Nand your family disappears,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:17.72,0:38:20.39,Default,,0,0,0,,and the indebtedness,\Nand then you lose,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:20.39,0:38:24.39,Default,,0,0,0,,they take away your credit card.\NSo the destruction and the destitution,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:24.39,0:38:30.39,Default,,0,0,0,,and of course the inner destruction is going on,\Nand that's what eventually brings people
Dialogue: 0,0:38:30.39,0:38:34.58,Default,,0,0,0,,into seeking help.\NThe energy field of courage then is crucial
Dialogue: 0,0:38:34.58,0:38:39.58,Default,,0,0,0,,because the antenna,\Nwhich was too negative, destructive,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:39.58,0:38:44.58,Default,,0,0,0,,and pulling into the person's life\Nall that is destructive in the universe,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:44.58,0:38:47.58,Default,,0,0,0,,now goes neutral.\NSo that process now,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:47.58,0:38:50.58,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd say the person is equally constructive\Nand destructive,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:50.58,0:38:54.58,Default,,0,0,0,,so that it neutralizes.\NThe antenna now goes neutral,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:54.58,0:38:59.58,Default,,0,0,0,,and the energy field is no longer reversed.\N200 is a lot of energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:59.58,0:39:02.58,Default,,0,0,0,,It gives the person the capacity to face,\Nto cope,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:02.58,0:39:07.74,Default,,0,0,0,,to go into appropriate action.\NAnd the process going on in consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:39:07.74,0:39:12.22,Default,,0,0,0,,is one of empowerment.\NAnd how does that come about?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:12.22,0:39:18.47,Default,,0,0,0,,It comes about as a result,\Nhow does the energy field reverse itself?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:18.47,0:39:24.47,Default,,0,0,0,,It comes about as a result of telling the truth.\NSo that, which is below the line,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:24.47,0:39:28.86,Default,,0,0,0,,victim,\Nis the selling out of the truth about yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:28.86,0:39:34.86,Default,,0,0,0,,The selling out of the truth reverses the energy field\Nand brings to the person destruction.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:34.86,0:39:40.17,Default,,0,0,0,,The way out, then,\Nis by stating the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:40.17,0:39:45.17,Default,,0,0,0,,The difficulty is a person down at this level\Nlooks within himself and says,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:45.17,0:39:48.17,Default,,0,0,0,,if I looked at the truth,\NI wouldn't be able to handle it.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:48.17,0:39:54.17,Default,,0,0,0,,And you will hear people in the 12-step groups\Nwho will tell you they've been in the program for years.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:54.17,0:39:56.17,Default,,0,0,0,,They've taken the first step,\Nmaybe the second step,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:56.17,0:39:59.46,Default,,0,0,0,,the third step,\Nthey even do 12-step work.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:59.46,0:40:03.46,Default,,0,0,0,,But the fourth step,\Nwhich is one of a personal fearless moral inventory,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:03.46,0:40:08.87,Default,,0,0,0,,many of them can't handle.\NThe reason is because the person looks at all this
Dialogue: 0,0:40:08.87,0:40:11.87,Default,,0,0,0,,and they say,\Nthis person here,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:11.87,0:40:16.87,Default,,0,0,0,,this person here,\Na reversed 100 person that I am,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:16.87,0:40:22.42,Default,,0,0,0,,cannot handle what's going to come up\Nif I start telling the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:22.42,0:40:27.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course, what they don't know is that the minute you do,\Nyou see you're walking off a cliff,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:27.61,0:40:30.61,Default,,0,0,0,,you don't know it,\Nbut when you do walk off the cliff and tell the truth,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:30.61,0:40:35.61,Default,,0,0,0,,what happens is you pull yourself from the universe,\Nthe power to face what comes up
Dialogue: 0,0:40:35.61,0:40:41.67,Default,,0,0,0,,as a result of telling the truth.\NBut you don't get the power until you do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:41.67,0:40:45.67,Default,,0,0,0,,So that's the first step then in the 12-step programs.\NAdmit it,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:45.67,0:40:52.67,Default,,0,0,0,,we are powerless over some addictive substance\Nor people do it in their daily life
Dialogue: 0,0:40:52.67,0:40:56.67,Default,,0,0,0,,who are not into the addictions.\NThe minute you admit the truth about something,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:56.67,0:41:00.67,Default,,0,0,0,,then this reversity stops.\NThe energy field goes neutral.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:00.67,0:41:03.67,Default,,0,0,0,,You pull to yourself,\Nthe energy field is 200,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:03.67,0:41:06.67,Default,,0,0,0,,which has,\Nthe capacity to face, to cope,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:06.67,0:41:10.67,Default,,0,0,0,,and to handle it with appropriate action.\NWhat has the power?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:10.67,0:41:14.67,Default,,0,0,0,,The energy field has the power.\NThe energy field is what has the power to handle it.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:14.67,0:41:20.67,Default,,0,0,0,,So you summon to yourself an energy field\Nthat has the power to handle it for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:20.67,0:41:27.67,Default,,0,0,0,,And as your own consciousness gets higher,\Nyou realize that it is being done like through you.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:27.67,0:41:31.67,Default,,0,0,0,,It is not your personal self.\NYour personal self has summoned it
Dialogue: 0,0:41:31.67,0:41:35.67,Default,,0,0,0,,through its own free will.\NIt has summoned it forth,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:35.67,0:41:40.96,Default,,0,0,0,,but now it is the field that is handling it.\NYou move up to the next higher level then,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:40.96,0:41:45.96,Default,,0,0,0,,the courage to face, to cope,\Nto take appropriate action in the addictions.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:45.96,0:41:49.96,Default,,0,0,0,,In the addictions and to let go the resistance.\NTo let go the resistance.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:49.96,0:41:54.12,Default,,0,0,0,,And through that empowerment now,\Nto let go resisting
Dialogue: 0,0:41:54.12,0:41:59.44,Default,,0,0,0,,and move up through an energy field which,\Nwe calibrate out at about 250.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:59.44,0:42:05.44,Default,,0,0,0,,And that's often accompanied by a feeling of detachment.\NThat this is, it's all okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:05.44,0:42:09.57,Default,,0,0,0,,It's okay if this happens.\NIt's okay if it doesn't happen.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:09.57,0:42:18.16,Default,,0,0,0,,And the process going on in consciousness,\Nwe say is the person has become released.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:18.16,0:42:22.16,Default,,0,0,0,,They've become released in that they've let go,\Ntrying to control it.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:22.16,0:42:26.19,Default,,0,0,0,,They have let go the resistance to however it goes.\NSo they say,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:26.19,0:42:32.42,Default,,0,0,0,,if I get a new car, that's great.\NAnd if I don't get a new car, that's great.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:32.42,0:42:36.42,Default,,0,0,0,,This company wants to keep me, swell.\NAnd if they want to let me go,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:36.42,0:42:40.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll find another job.\NSo, it's a great field to be in
Dialogue: 0,0:42:40.42,0:42:44.42,Default,,0,0,0,,if you've been down here.\NTo be up in neutral at least,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:44.42,0:42:49.42,Default,,0,0,0,,you don't have the painful experiences.\NYou see, in courage, you have the energy
Dialogue: 0,0:42:49.42,0:42:53.93,Default,,0,0,0,,to handle these lower feelings,\Nbut they haven't disappeared.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:53.93,0:42:57.93,Default,,0,0,0,,The person in courage goes to ask the boss for a raise.\NHis stomach is in a knot.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:57.93,0:43:01.93,Default,,0,0,0,,See, his stomach can be in a knot.\NHe can be run by this desire.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:01.93,0:43:06.93,Default,,0,0,0,,He can be angry that he's got to go and ask in the first place.\NHe can be resentful and have all kinds of self-pity down here.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:06.93,0:43:11.93,Default,,0,0,0,,This value to the company wasn't recognized\Nand he had to go and ask for it, etc.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:11.93,0:43:17.54,Default,,0,0,0,,So he has all these negative feelings.\NBut the courage, the power of courage at 200
Dialogue: 0,0:43:17.54,0:43:21.57,Default,,0,0,0,,has the power to handle that.\NAnd so he acts appropriately
Dialogue: 0,0:43:21.57,0:43:25.57,Default,,0,0,0,,despite the negative feelings.\NAs you move up into neutral,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:25.57,0:43:31.57,Default,,0,0,0,,where you become no longer attached to outcome,\Nthen you energize,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:31.57,0:43:36.57,Default,,0,0,0,,you get a feeling of being released about the matter,\Nand these feelings begin to disappear.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:36.57,0:43:40.57,Default,,0,0,0,,These feelings disappear.\NWhen you're totally released on it, it's great.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:40.57,0:43:44.57,Default,,0,0,0,,The boss gives you the raise, fantastic.\NAnd if he doesn't, you live with it.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:44.57,0:43:50.57,Default,,0,0,0,,So it's a great field to be in\Nas compared to having your stomach in a knot.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:50.57,0:43:55.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course, the person at the bottom wouldn't even ask for a raise\Nbecause, in his view, he would be worthless
Dialogue: 0,0:43:55.57,0:43:59.82,Default,,0,0,0,,and the boss would never give him a raise anyway.\NSo you have to move up higher
Dialogue: 0,0:43:59.82,0:44:03.82,Default,,0,0,0,,to even take appropriate action.\NSo this allows the person
Dialogue: 0,0:44:03.82,0:44:10.08,Default,,0,0,0,,to become easygoing\Nand move up into the next energy field called acceptance.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:10.08,0:44:15.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Acceptance is a much higher field.\NIt calibrates out at 380.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:15.08,0:44:21.72,Default,,0,0,0,,At that level, the person is easygoing\Nand confident and capable.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:21.72,0:44:26.72,Default,,0,0,0,,And we see that there's the beginning now\Nof a transformation in consciousness,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:26.72,0:44:31.72,Default,,0,0,0,,a growing awareness.\NAnd what is the growing awareness from?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:31.72,0:44:35.72,Default,,0,0,0,,The growing awareness is coming from\Nthe realization
Dialogue: 0,0:44:35.72,0:44:39.72,Default,,0,0,0,,that the power,\Nthe power to be happy,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:39.72,0:44:45.75,Default,,0,0,0,,the source of happiness in my life is within me.\NI'm the one that decides
Dialogue: 0,0:44:45.75,0:44:53.65,Default,,0,0,0,,whether I'm going to be successful or happy\Nin any situation or relationship or position.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:53.65,0:44:57.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Below the level of courage,\Neverybody, because they're victim,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:57.65,0:45:01.90,Default,,0,0,0,,thinks that it is out there.\NThe power is out there.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:01.90,0:45:05.90,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the Cadillac that will do it for me.\NIt's the position, it's the title, it's the address,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:05.90,0:45:09.90,Default,,0,0,0,,it's the suit of clothes.\NIt's something out there will do it for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:09.90,0:45:14.86,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the relationship,\Nit's the her in my life or the him in my life.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:14.86,0:45:18.86,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the PhD degree or whatever.\NThat's what's going to do it for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:18.86,0:45:23.86,Default,,0,0,0,,But as you move up to this higher energy field,\Nthere's the realization
Dialogue: 0,0:45:23.86,0:45:28.86,Default,,0,0,0,,that the power to create happiness and success in my life\Nlies within me and me alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:28.86,0:45:33.86,Default,,0,0,0,,And it's arising out of my positions,\Nit's arising out of my decisions,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:33.86,0:45:37.86,Default,,0,0,0,,it's arising out of my intentions,\Nmy goals, my purposes.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:37.86,0:45:43.86,Default,,0,0,0,,It's arising out of that which I value.\NAnd what I value is arising out of the meaning.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:43.86,0:45:47.86,Default,,0,0,0,,It's arising out of the context.\NIt's beginning to arise out of that which I am.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:47.86,0:45:52.86,Default,,0,0,0,,So that transformation of that awareness\Nthen gives the person a great deal more power.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:52.86,0:45:59.28,Default,,0,0,0,,They're no longer dependent on the world as the source.\NSee, down here the world has to amuse you
Dialogue: 0,0:45:59.28,0:46:06.70,Default,,0,0,0,,and there's nothing more panicky than your TV set going out.\NOr being all alone by yourself with nothing to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:06.70,0:46:09.70,Default,,0,0,0,,See?\NYou have to sit in a bus station for three hours
Dialogue: 0,0:46:09.70,0:46:13.86,Default,,0,0,0,,with nothing to do.\NAnd the magazine stand is closed
Dialogue: 0,0:46:13.86,0:46:17.86,Default,,0,0,0,,and there's no TV and there's no radio.\NAnd there you are all by yourself in a bus station
Dialogue: 0,0:46:17.86,0:46:20.86,Default,,0,0,0,,in the middle of nowhere\Nand you've got four hours to kill.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:20.86,0:46:25.92,Default,,0,0,0,,This would be death to these people.\NBecause there's nothing out there to hang on to.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:25.92,0:46:28.92,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no beauty out there.\NThere's no aesthetic amusement.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:28.92,0:46:33.34,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no action.\NHere a person would say,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:33.34,0:46:37.34,Default,,0,0,0,,fantastic, wow, I've got three and a half hours\Nand I've got so much stuff to work on myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:37.34,0:46:40.34,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, what a lucky break.\NI've got four hours.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:40.34,0:46:44.34,Default,,0,0,0,,I can barely catch up in four hours.\NAll the stuff I've got to handle in my life.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:44.34,0:46:48.46,Default,,0,0,0,,They would think it's great.\NSo that power then,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:48.46,0:46:52.46,Default,,0,0,0,,that person in that energy state knows\Nif you drop them in a desert island someplace
Dialogue: 0,0:46:52.46,0:46:57.46,Default,,0,0,0,,in the middle of the Atlantic or Pacific Ocean\Nand if you come back a year later
Dialogue: 0,0:46:57.46,0:47:01.46,Default,,0,0,0,,you'll have a coconut factory going.\NYou'll be teaching the natives French.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:01.46,0:47:04.46,Default,,0,0,0,,You'll have found a cute little native girl.\NYou'll build a tree house.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:04.46,0:47:08.46,Default,,0,0,0,,That capacity to create for yourself\Nout of what is around you,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:08.46,0:47:10.46,Default,,0,0,0,,to make a garden there,\Nto grow things there,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:10.46,0:47:15.46,Default,,0,0,0,,to create an industry,\Nto create something where the energy flows back to you
Dialogue: 0,0:47:15.46,0:47:20.46,Default,,0,0,0,,with the happiness of that.\NSo we all know that level in ourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:20.46,0:47:26.46,Default,,0,0,0,,What the world calls important\Ndoesn't really mean anything
Dialogue: 0,0:47:26.46,0:47:30.46,Default,,0,0,0,,when you just found the missing nut\Nthat allowed you to fix the fan.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:30.46,0:47:35.46,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, you know how happy that is?\NOr you just found your crochet hook
Dialogue: 0,0:47:35.46,0:47:40.46,Default,,0,0,0,,that you can't finish the thing with.\NIt's the little things that make your whole day delightful.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:40.46,0:47:44.46,Default,,0,0,0,,And how many times in my life\Nhas it become a delight over some little thing, you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:44.46,0:47:46.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Like I just finished a chicken coop\Nand the chickens are happy.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:46.46,0:47:50.46,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, what could make you happier, you know?\NWhat the world thinks and all the tiles on it
Dialogue: 0,0:47:50.46,0:47:53.46,Default,,0,0,0,,doesn't mean anything\Nbecause what you're experiencing is joy
Dialogue: 0,0:47:53.46,0:47:57.46,Default,,0,0,0,,with the right now,\Nwith the right now of what it all is to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:57.46,0:48:01.46,Default,,0,0,0,,The joy of your own existence.\NTo experience the joy of your own existence
Dialogue: 0,0:48:01.46,0:48:05.46,Default,,0,0,0,,then moves you up\Nand you're moving up to the next energy level.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:05.46,0:48:10.53,Default,,0,0,0,,That's what we call love.\NLove is, in this context then,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:10.53,0:48:16.53,Default,,0,0,0,,calibrates at an energy field of 500.\NIt is the beginning of happiness.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:16.53,0:48:21.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Happiness, if you calibrate it, comes out at 500.\NA very crucial level,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:21.53,0:48:25.53,Default,,0,0,0,,a very crucial level\Nfor us to work in the addictions
Dialogue: 0,0:48:25.53,0:48:30.53,Default,,0,0,0,,because we're moving into the energy field\Nof the self-help groups.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:30.53,0:48:36.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Alcoholics Anonymous calibrates out at 540.\NThe energy fields of love
Dialogue: 0,0:48:36.10,0:48:42.10,Default,,0,0,0,,and these are not the sentimental emotionalism of love\Nthat the world talks about
Dialogue: 0,0:48:42.10,0:48:48.52,Default,,0,0,0,,but a powerful, stable, unconditional energy field\Nthat you set by your own intention,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:48.52,0:48:54.32,Default,,0,0,0,,by your own decision,\Nby that to which you say yes in your life.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:54.32,0:49:00.32,Default,,0,0,0,,The energy field of 500.\NAs you move into the energy fields of 500 and up,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:00.32,0:49:04.32,Default,,0,0,0,,about 540,\NAlcoholics Anonymous really calibrates at 540
Dialogue: 0,0:49:04.32,0:49:09.32,Default,,0,0,0,,which is the energy field of healing.\NWhen you calibrate the energy field of healing,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:09.32,0:49:15.32,Default,,0,0,0,,it is around 540.\NThat means that the energy field alone of the group,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:15.32,0:49:19.32,Default,,0,0,0,,irrespective of what they talk about,\Nirrespective of the whole program,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:19.32,0:49:25.38,Default,,0,0,0,,the wording, the phrasing, the languaging of it,\Nthe energy field of that
Dialogue: 0,0:49:25.38,0:49:30.38,Default,,0,0,0,,is in itself healing.\NAnd therefore you hear statements
Dialogue: 0,0:49:30.38,0:49:33.38,Default,,0,0,0,,in which this is intuited.\NThey will say,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:33.38,0:49:36.38,Default,,0,0,0,,just bring the body,\Njust bring the body.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:36.38,0:49:40.38,Default,,0,0,0,,We know that people get just as sober\Nif they're ordered there by the court
Dialogue: 0,0:49:40.38,0:49:44.38,Default,,0,0,0,,as if they go there voluntarily.\NAnd somebody I know
Dialogue: 0,0:49:44.38,0:49:48.77,Default,,0,0,0,,quite well in one of the groups\Nwas just ordered there to the court
Dialogue: 0,0:49:48.77,0:49:52.77,Default,,0,0,0,,because he had three DWIs\Nand he had a choice between a year in jail
Dialogue: 0,0:49:52.77,0:49:54.77,Default,,0,0,0,,or going to AA.\NAt the end of a year,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:54.77,0:49:57.77,Default,,0,0,0,,when his sentence was up,\Nhe wouldn't have left it for the world
Dialogue: 0,0:49:57.77,0:50:03.38,Default,,0,0,0,,because his own consciousness\Nhad become transformed.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:03.38,0:50:06.38,Default,,0,0,0,,So this is sort of like,\Nyou might say,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:06.38,0:50:10.38,Default,,0,0,0,,an electromagnetic field.\NIt's a field phenomenon.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:10.38,0:50:14.38,Default,,0,0,0,,An energy field of 540\Nheals anything you put in it.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:14.38,0:50:18.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Sick rabbits,\Nwounded legs,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:18.38,0:50:22.38,Default,,0,0,0,,people in despair,\Npeople addicted to substances,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:22.38,0:50:25.38,Default,,0,0,0,,whatever.\NIf you picture it like an impersonal
Dialogue: 0,0:50:25.38,0:50:28.38,Default,,0,0,0,,electromagnetic energy field then,\Nwith a certain power,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:28.38,0:50:32.38,Default,,0,0,0,,a power that we calibrate,\Nlet's say you set the dial at 540,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:32.38,0:50:36.38,Default,,0,0,0,,then whatever you set in it,\Nset in it is going to begin to heal
Dialogue: 0,0:50:36.38,0:50:39.38,Default,,0,0,0,,itself.\NThe kind of love we're talking about
Dialogue: 0,0:50:39.38,0:50:41.38,Default,,0,0,0,,never dies.\NThere isn't a such thing
Dialogue: 0,0:50:41.38,0:50:43.44,Default,,0,0,0,,as unconditional love dying.\NWhy?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:43.44,0:50:46.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Because it is a decision\Nthat you make within yourself
Dialogue: 0,0:50:46.44,0:50:50.44,Default,,0,0,0,,that sets up an energy field\Nwhich is stable.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:50.44,0:50:53.44,Default,,0,0,0,,So that which is unconditional love\Nis unchanging.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:53.44,0:50:56.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Unchanging.\NWithin the energy field
Dialogue: 0,0:50:56.60,0:50:59.60,Default,,0,0,0,,of unconditional love\Nto which you've committed yourself,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:59.60,0:51:04.63,Default,,0,0,0,,the negative emotions may come and go.\NYou may hate the person.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:04.63,0:51:06.63,Default,,0,0,0,,I hate you.\NI can't stand you.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:06.63,0:51:09.63,Default,,0,0,0,,That's a passing emotion.\NAnd the person's unconditional love
Dialogue: 0,0:51:09.63,0:51:13.63,Default,,0,0,0,,has not changed their commitment.\NIt has not changed their commitment at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:13.63,0:51:17.63,Default,,0,0,0,,That's a passing emotion,\Nbut it is only passing within
Dialogue: 0,0:51:17.63,0:51:20.63,Default,,0,0,0,,a greater energy field.\NAnd of course they know
Dialogue: 0,0:51:20.63,0:51:22.63,Default,,0,0,0,,they're going to forgive the other person.\NAnd of course they know
Dialogue: 0,0:51:22.63,0:51:24.63,Default,,0,0,0,,that they're going to make up.\NAnd of course they know
Dialogue: 0,0:51:24.63,0:51:27.63,Default,,0,0,0,,they're not going to hang on\Nto this resentment any longer
Dialogue: 0,0:51:27.63,0:51:31.63,Default,,0,0,0,,than it takes to get rid of it.\NSo the person in this level then
Dialogue: 0,0:51:31.63,0:51:36.63,Default,,0,0,0,,is characterized in their emotional state\Nby a caring for,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:36.63,0:51:38.63,Default,,0,0,0,,a nurturing,\Na support,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:38.63,0:51:43.08,Default,,0,0,0,,a willingness to forgive,\Na willingness to understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:43.08,0:51:46.08,Default,,0,0,0,,So what is the question then\Nin the person's mind
Dialogue: 0,0:51:46.08,0:51:49.08,Default,,0,0,0,,in this energy field\Nis to understand that,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:49.08,0:51:54.21,Default,,0,0,0,,to understand that.\NSee, down here the idea is to make it wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:54.21,0:51:58.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Who's right and who's wrong.\NHere the intention is right and wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:58.21,0:52:01.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Here the intention is not even interested\Nin right and wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:01.21,0:52:05.24,Default,,0,0,0,,It's totally irrelevant.\NIf you get into an argument,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:05.24,0:52:07.24,Default,,0,0,0,,if people in this level\Nget into an argument,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:07.24,0:52:09.24,Default,,0,0,0,,nobody even cares\Nif it's right or wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:09.24,0:52:11.24,Default,,0,0,0,,What they want to know\Nis what's out with us.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:11.24,0:52:14.24,Default,,0,0,0,,What don't we understand?\NI mean, where is it coming from?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:14.24,0:52:16.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Is it karma?\NYou know what I mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:16.24,0:52:19.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Is it a past life?\NIs it something going on
Dialogue: 0,0:52:19.24,0:52:22.24,Default,,0,0,0,,that I'm not aware of?\NWhat is it that's not healed in me
Dialogue: 0,0:52:22.24,0:52:25.24,Default,,0,0,0,,that's bringing it up?\NBecause there's the beginning
Dialogue: 0,0:52:25.24,0:52:29.24,Default,,0,0,0,,of a revelation, you see.\NThe beginning of transformation now
Dialogue: 0,0:52:29.24,0:52:32.24,Default,,0,0,0,,is bringing you\Nto certain inner revelations.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:32.24,0:52:34.24,Default,,0,0,0,,And you begin to realize\Nthat when things
Dialogue: 0,0:52:34.24,0:52:37.24,Default,,0,0,0,,are not going smoothly,\Nthat it's merely something
Dialogue: 0,0:52:37.24,0:52:39.24,Default,,0,0,0,,to be handled.\NIt's something that's
Dialogue: 0,0:52:39.24,0:52:41.24,Default,,0,0,0,,not understood.\NAnd then when it's
Dialogue: 0,0:52:41.24,0:52:43.24,Default,,0,0,0,,correctly understood,\Nbecause it is now held
Dialogue: 0,0:52:43.24,0:52:46.24,Default,,0,0,0,,from the viewpoint\Nof understanding,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:46.24,0:52:48.24,Default,,0,0,0,,the understanding itself\Nheals that.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:48.24,0:52:51.24,Default,,0,0,0,,So that you can't\Nstay mad at a person
Dialogue: 0,0:52:51.24,0:52:53.24,Default,,0,0,0,,in the field\Nof unconditional love.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:53.24,0:52:55.24,Default,,0,0,0,,And of course,\Nwe're all aware of that.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:55.24,0:52:59.56,Default,,0,0,0,,That's one of the whole intentions\Nof the consciousness movement
Dialogue: 0,0:52:59.56,0:53:02.56,Default,,0,0,0,,and all that is called\NNew Age and etc.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:02.56,0:53:04.69,Default,,0,0,0,,As we know,\Nthat a resentment
Dialogue: 0,0:53:04.69,0:53:06.69,Default,,0,0,0,,is your problem\Nto handle and get off,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:06.69,0:53:08.69,Default,,0,0,0,,you see.\NTo get off the resentment
Dialogue: 0,0:53:08.69,0:53:10.69,Default,,0,0,0,,is your problem.\NIt is not up
Dialogue: 0,0:53:10.69,0:53:12.69,Default,,0,0,0,,to the other problem\Nto change.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:12.69,0:53:15.07,Default,,0,0,0,,So if you don't like the fact\Nthat he wears a vest
Dialogue: 0,0:53:15.07,0:53:17.07,Default,,0,0,0,,all the time,\Nthat's your problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:17.07,0:53:19.07,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not the other fellow's\Nproblem to no longer
Dialogue: 0,0:53:19.07,0:53:21.07,Default,,0,0,0,,wear a vest.\NIt's your problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:21.07,0:53:24.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Why that bothers you.\NSo that brings us
Dialogue: 0,0:53:24.07,0:53:26.07,Default,,0,0,0,,then into a powerful\Nenergy field
Dialogue: 0,0:53:26.07,0:53:29.07,Default,,0,0,0,,which is coming out\Nof our intention
Dialogue: 0,0:53:29.07,0:53:32.07,Default,,0,0,0,,to be that kind of person.\NSo we might say
Dialogue: 0,0:53:32.07,0:53:35.07,Default,,0,0,0,,that we could call\Nthis level here
Dialogue: 0,0:53:35.07,0:53:37.07,Default,,0,0,0,,lovingness.\NLovingness.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:37.07,0:53:39.07,Default,,0,0,0,,We say that a person\Nlike that,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:39.07,0:53:42.26,Default,,0,0,0,,what they're showing\Nis lovingness.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:42.26,0:53:45.26,Default,,0,0,0,,This quality goes on\Nwith them all the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:45.26,0:53:48.39,Default,,0,0,0,,So their relationship\Nto things
Dialogue: 0,0:53:48.39,0:53:52.39,Default,,0,0,0,,is one of lovingness.\NTo nurture that beauty
Dialogue: 0,0:53:52.39,0:53:54.74,Default,,0,0,0,,around them.\NTheir relationship
Dialogue: 0,0:53:54.74,0:53:56.74,Default,,0,0,0,,to animals\Nis one of lovingness.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:56.74,0:53:58.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Their relationships\Nto all things
Dialogue: 0,0:53:58.74,0:54:01.74,Default,,0,0,0,,is one of lovingness.\NA lovingness towards life
Dialogue: 0,0:54:01.74,0:54:03.74,Default,,0,0,0,,and a lovingness\Ntowards life.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:03.74,0:54:05.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Towards beauty\Nand the desire
Dialogue: 0,0:54:05.74,0:54:08.13,Default,,0,0,0,,to support that\Nand understand that.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:08.13,0:54:10.13,Default,,0,0,0,,So relationships\Ncoming out of that
Dialogue: 0,0:54:10.13,0:54:13.13,Default,,0,0,0,,are then unconditional.\NMeaning non-judgmental.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:13.13,0:54:16.13,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no interest\Nin rightness
Dialogue: 0,0:54:16.13,0:54:18.13,Default,,0,0,0,,and wrongness.\NSo characteristic
Dialogue: 0,0:54:18.13,0:54:20.13,Default,,0,0,0,,of the 12-step group.\NSo let's say
Dialogue: 0,0:54:20.13,0:54:24.13,Default,,0,0,0,,somebody who's been in AA\Nwould have a slip.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:24.13,0:54:26.13,Default,,0,0,0,,And while they're\Non the slip
Dialogue: 0,0:54:26.13,0:54:28.13,Default,,0,0,0,,they shot three people\Nand ran over four infants
Dialogue: 0,0:54:28.13,0:54:31.13,Default,,0,0,0,,and destroyed a building.\NWhen they come back
Dialogue: 0,0:54:31.13,0:54:33.13,Default,,0,0,0,,to the group\Nwhat does everybody say?
Dialogue: 0,0:54:33.13,0:54:35.13,Default,,0,0,0,,George.\NIt's wonderful
Dialogue: 0,0:54:35.13,0:54:37.13,Default,,0,0,0,,to have you back.\NYou know what I mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:54:37.13,0:54:39.13,Default,,0,0,0,,It's wonderful\Nto have you back.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:39.13,0:54:42.13,Default,,0,0,0,,There is no interest\Nin a moralistic condemnation.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:42.13,0:54:44.13,Default,,0,0,0,,There is only\Nan interest
Dialogue: 0,0:54:44.13,0:54:46.13,Default,,0,0,0,,in what the person is.\NAnd it's because
Dialogue: 0,0:54:46.13,0:54:48.13,Default,,0,0,0,,they're relating\Nthey're beginning
Dialogue: 0,0:54:48.13,0:54:50.13,Default,,0,0,0,,to relate now\Nto the person's beingness.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:50.13,0:54:53.58,Default,,0,0,0,,That which they really are.\NSo the mother
Dialogue: 0,0:54:53.58,0:54:55.58,Default,,0,0,0,,who visits her son\Nin prison
Dialogue: 0,0:54:55.58,0:54:57.58,Default,,0,0,0,,for 20 years\Na murderer
Dialogue: 0,0:54:57.58,0:54:59.58,Default,,0,0,0,,in prison\Nand when I was
Dialogue: 0,0:54:59.58,0:55:01.58,Default,,0,0,0,,a doctor\Nin the state hospitals
Dialogue: 0,0:55:01.58,0:55:03.58,Default,,0,0,0,,we had situations\Nexactly like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:03.58,0:55:05.58,Default,,0,0,0,,People\Nextremely psychotic
Dialogue: 0,0:55:05.58,0:55:07.58,Default,,0,0,0,,and in their\Npsychotic behavior
Dialogue: 0,0:55:07.58,0:55:09.58,Default,,0,0,0,,they had done\Nreally terrible things
Dialogue: 0,0:55:09.58,0:55:11.58,Default,,0,0,0,,almost a terrible\Ndimension.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:11.58,0:55:13.58,Default,,0,0,0,,And yet the mothers\Nthe families
Dialogue: 0,0:55:13.58,0:55:15.58,Default,,0,0,0,,would come\Nand visit them
Dialogue: 0,0:55:15.58,0:55:17.58,Default,,0,0,0,,throughout the rest\Nof their life.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:17.58,0:55:19.58,Default,,0,0,0,,So the unconditional love\Nthen
Dialogue: 0,0:55:19.58,0:55:21.58,Default,,0,0,0,,overlooks\Nwhat the behavior is.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:21.58,0:55:23.58,Default,,0,0,0,,It says\Nthat which is
Dialogue: 0,0:55:23.58,0:55:25.58,Default,,0,0,0,,the behavior\Nis coming out
Dialogue: 0,0:55:25.58,0:55:27.58,Default,,0,0,0,,of that\Nwhich is not understood.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:27.58,0:55:29.58,Default,,0,0,0,,It's coming out\Nof illness
Dialogue: 0,0:55:29.58,0:55:31.58,Default,,0,0,0,,it's coming out\Nof unknowingness
Dialogue: 0,0:55:31.58,0:55:33.58,Default,,0,0,0,,it's coming out\Nof ignorance
Dialogue: 0,0:55:33.58,0:55:36.58,Default,,0,0,0,,and that is not really\Nsomething greater than that.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:36.58,0:55:38.58,Default,,0,0,0,,And so\Nin Outlawics Anonymous
Dialogue: 0,0:55:38.58,0:55:40.58,Default,,0,0,0,,then what the people\Nrelate to
Dialogue: 0,0:55:40.58,0:55:42.58,Default,,0,0,0,,is that which you really are.\NAnd the behavior
Dialogue: 0,0:55:42.58,0:55:44.58,Default,,0,0,0,,is overlooked.\NNobody cares
Dialogue: 0,0:55:44.58,0:55:47.67,Default,,0,0,0,,what you have.\NSee at the bottom
Dialogue: 0,0:55:47.67,0:55:49.67,Default,,0,0,0,,of the box\Npeople are interested
Dialogue: 0,0:55:49.67,0:55:51.67,Default,,0,0,0,,in what you have.\NWhat you have.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:51.67,0:55:53.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Possessions\Nand titles
Dialogue: 0,0:55:53.67,0:55:55.67,Default,,0,0,0,,and appearances\Nand things
Dialogue: 0,0:55:55.67,0:55:57.67,Default,,0,0,0,,all having to do\Nwith have.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:57.67,0:55:59.67,Default,,0,0,0,,In the middle of the box\Npeople are interested
Dialogue: 0,0:55:59.67,0:56:01.67,Default,,0,0,0,,in what you do.\NSee your titles
Dialogue: 0,0:56:01.67,0:56:03.67,Default,,0,0,0,,what you do\Nin the world
Dialogue: 0,0:56:03.67,0:56:05.67,Default,,0,0,0,,becomes very important.\NBut as you move towards
Dialogue: 0,0:56:05.67,0:56:07.67,Default,,0,0,0,,the top of the box\Nwhat people are interested in
Dialogue: 0,0:56:07.67,0:56:09.67,Default,,0,0,0,,is what you are.\NWhat you are.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:09.67,0:56:11.67,Default,,0,0,0,,And so\Ntherefore
Dialogue: 0,0:56:11.67,0:56:14.47,Default,,0,0,0,,in recovery\Nfrom addictions
Dialogue: 0,0:56:14.47,0:56:17.46,Default,,0,0,0,,in AA\Nfor instance
Dialogue: 0,0:56:17.46,0:56:19.46,Default,,0,0,0,,nobody cares\Nabout what you have.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:19.46,0:56:21.46,Default,,0,0,0,,You can know somebody\Nfor 20 years
Dialogue: 0,0:56:21.46,0:56:23.46,Default,,0,0,0,,and have them\Ndisliked
Dialogue: 0,0:56:23.46,0:56:25.46,Default,,0,0,0,,about what they have\Nor interest.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:25.46,0:56:27.62,Default,,0,0,0,,You may even\Nafter 20 years
Dialogue: 0,0:56:27.62,0:56:29.62,Default,,0,0,0,,still not really\Neven know
Dialogue: 0,0:56:29.62,0:56:31.62,Default,,0,0,0,,what they do\Ndespite the fact
Dialogue: 0,0:56:31.62,0:56:33.62,Default,,0,0,0,,that you've talked\Nto them
Dialogue: 0,0:56:33.62,0:56:35.62,Default,,0,0,0,,on the most intimate level\Nabout the most mind-boggling
Dialogue: 0,0:56:35.62,0:56:37.62,Default,,0,0,0,,thing anybody else\Nin the world about.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:37.62,0:56:39.88,Default,,0,0,0,,You still at this point\Ndon't even know
Dialogue: 0,0:56:39.88,0:56:41.88,Default,,0,0,0,,what the person does.\NWhat was it
Dialogue: 0,0:56:41.88,0:56:43.88,Default,,0,0,0,,you do again?\NI forget what it is
Dialogue: 0,0:56:43.88,0:56:45.88,Default,,0,0,0,,an engineer or something\NI don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:45.88,0:56:47.88,Default,,0,0,0,,What the person is\Nthat is what
Dialogue: 0,0:56:47.88,0:56:49.88,Default,,0,0,0,,is all important.\NIt's because
Dialogue: 0,0:56:49.88,0:56:51.88,Default,,0,0,0,,of what they are\Nthat you honor them
Dialogue: 0,0:56:51.88,0:56:55.42,Default,,0,0,0,,and you protect them\Nand you support that
Dialogue: 0,0:56:55.42,0:56:57.42,Default,,0,0,0,,and you forgive them\Nand when they forget
Dialogue: 0,0:56:57.42,0:56:59.42,Default,,0,0,0,,the truth\Nof that which they are
Dialogue: 0,0:56:59.42,0:57:01.42,Default,,0,0,0,,then you hold that\Nfor them
Dialogue: 0,0:57:01.42,0:57:03.42,Default,,0,0,0,,and remind them\Nof that.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:03.42,0:57:05.90,Default,,0,0,0,,And how that\Npowerful energy
Dialogue: 0,0:57:05.90,0:57:07.90,Default,,0,0,0,,feels\Nthen you see
Dialogue: 0,0:57:07.90,0:57:09.90,Default,,0,0,0,,over on the right\Nwe said
Dialogue: 0,0:57:09.90,0:57:11.97,Default,,0,0,0,,a process\Na revelation.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:11.97,0:57:13.97,Default,,0,0,0,,So what's going on\Nwithin the brain
Dialogue: 0,0:57:13.97,0:57:16.06,Default,,0,0,0,,we sort of lost\Ntrack of the brain
Dialogue: 0,0:57:16.06,0:57:18.06,Default,,0,0,0,,here for a while.\NThe bottom
Dialogue: 0,0:57:18.06,0:57:20.06,Default,,0,0,0,,we had the death\Nhormone
Dialogue: 0,0:57:20.06,0:57:22.06,Default,,0,0,0,,the death enzyme\Nand then we had
Dialogue: 0,0:57:22.06,0:57:24.06,Default,,0,0,0,,depression\Nof neurotransmitters.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:24.06,0:57:26.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Up here we have\Na build up
Dialogue: 0,0:57:26.06,0:57:28.06,Default,,0,0,0,,up here we have\Na build up
Dialogue: 0,0:57:28.06,0:57:30.10,Default,,0,0,0,,of the neurotransmitters\Nyou know high levels
Dialogue: 0,0:57:30.10,0:57:32.10,Default,,0,0,0,,of norepinephrine\Nand serotonin
Dialogue: 0,0:57:32.10,0:57:34.10,Default,,0,0,0,,etc.\NAnd as we
Dialogue: 0,0:57:34.10,0:57:36.10,Default,,0,0,0,,get up here\Nwe get into
Dialogue: 0,0:57:36.10,0:57:38.32,Default,,0,0,0,,the release\Nand the release
Dialogue: 0,0:57:38.32,0:57:40.32,Default,,0,0,0,,of the endorphins\Nhaving to do
Dialogue: 0,0:57:40.32,0:57:42.32,Default,,0,0,0,,with the activation\Nof the pituitary gland
Dialogue: 0,0:57:42.32,0:57:44.32,Default,,0,0,0,,and as you get up\Nnear the top
Dialogue: 0,0:57:44.32,0:57:46.32,Default,,0,0,0,,having to do\Nwith the endorphins
Dialogue: 0,0:57:46.32,0:57:48.38,Default,,0,0,0,,having to do\Nwith the pineal gland
Dialogue: 0,0:57:48.38,0:57:50.38,Default,,0,0,0,,also\Nthat is of critical
Dialogue: 0,0:57:50.38,0:57:52.38,Default,,0,0,0,,importance\Nand there's a lot
Dialogue: 0,0:57:52.38,0:57:54.38,Default,,0,0,0,,of research\Ncoming out
Dialogue: 0,0:57:54.38,0:57:56.38,Default,,0,0,0,,in neuroscience\Nof course
Dialogue: 0,0:57:56.38,0:57:58.38,Default,,0,0,0,,having to do\Nwith endorphins
Dialogue: 0,0:57:58.38,0:58:00.38,Default,,0,0,0,,and the part\Nthat they play
Dialogue: 0,0:58:00.38,0:58:02.38,Default,,0,0,0,,in addiction\Nand that is a whole
Dialogue: 0,0:58:02.38,0:58:04.38,Default,,0,0,0,,subject in itself\Nwe don't have time
Dialogue: 0,0:58:04.38,0:58:06.38,Default,,0,0,0,,today\Nto go into that
Dialogue: 0,0:58:06.38,0:58:08.38,Default,,0,0,0,,but that is a whole\Nsubject
Dialogue: 0,0:58:18.26,0:58:20.38,Default,,0,0,0,,in the endorphins\Nand the treatments
Dialogue: 0,0:58:20.38,0:58:22.38,Default,,0,0,0,,that are based\Nin the illogic theories
Dialogue: 0,0:58:22.38,0:58:24.38,Default,,0,0,0,,that are based\Non the presence
Dialogue: 0,0:58:24.38,0:58:26.38,Default,,0,0,0,,or the absence\Nof the endorphins
Dialogue: 0,0:58:26.38,0:58:28.38,Default,,0,0,0,,the most current\None being that
Dialogue: 0,0:58:28.38,0:58:30.38,Default,,0,0,0,,alcoholics\Nand others
Dialogue: 0,0:58:30.38,0:58:32.38,Default,,0,0,0,,have a deficiency\Nof these endorphins
Dialogue: 0,0:58:32.38,0:58:34.38,Default,,0,0,0,,and that the drug\Nreleases an endorphin
Dialogue: 0,0:58:34.38,0:58:36.38,Default,,0,0,0,,and allows the person\Nto feel
Dialogue: 0,0:58:36.38,0:58:38.38,Default,,0,0,0,,normal\Nto those endorphins
Dialogue: 0,0:58:38.38,0:58:40.77,Default,,0,0,0,,as you move\Nup
Dialogue: 0,0:58:40.77,0:58:42.77,Default,,0,0,0,,and then\Nbecause of
Dialogue: 0,0:58:42.77,0:58:44.77,Default,,0,0,0,,the\Nwhat's happening
Dialogue: 0,0:58:44.77,0:58:46.77,Default,,0,0,0,,out of this revelation\Nout of the release
Dialogue: 0,0:58:46.77,0:58:48.77,Default,,0,0,0,,of the endorphins\Nyou have awarenesses
Dialogue: 0,0:58:48.77,0:58:50.77,Default,,0,0,0,,now\Nthat move
Dialogue: 0,0:58:50.77,0:58:52.77,Default,,0,0,0,,the person\Nup into levels
Dialogue: 0,0:58:52.77,0:58:54.77,Default,,0,0,0,,of joyfulness\Nup into levels
Dialogue: 0,0:58:54.77,0:58:56.77,Default,,0,0,0,,of joyfulness\Nwhich calibrate
Dialogue: 0,0:58:56.77,0:58:58.77,Default,,0,0,0,,about 540\Nup into energy
Dialogue: 0,0:58:58.77,0:59:00.77,Default,,0,0,0,,levels of ecstasy\Nwhich calibrate
Dialogue: 0,0:59:00.77,0:59:02.86,Default,,0,0,0,,at about 560\Nyou start moving
Dialogue: 0,0:59:02.86,0:59:04.86,Default,,0,0,0,,into transfiguration\Nand states
Dialogue: 0,0:59:04.86,0:59:06.96,Default,,0,0,0,,of illumination\Nand you're moving
Dialogue: 0,0:59:06.96,0:59:08.96,Default,,0,0,0,,out towards\Nan energy field
Dialogue: 0,0:59:08.96,0:59:11.28,Default,,0,0,0,,which is right\Nabout the level
