Dialogue: 0,1:13:00.34,1:13:15.04,Default,,0,0,0,,and say yes to it. He has to say yes to every step of the way to get back to that mountain pass.\NAnd then he returns to Shangri-La, but this time it is different. He is now himself the one who
Dialogue: 0,1:13:15.04,1:13:32.54,Default,,0,0,0,,holds that for Shangri-La. You remember the old leader of the community had died in the interim,\Nand now he was the one holding that level of consciousness for the group. So the power then
Dialogue: 0,1:13:32.54,1:13:43.60,Default,,0,0,0,,of that experience, the power of that experience. So what happens of course with the drugs is the\Ndrugs don't have any power to create a state of highness. Drugs have no power at all. We will
Dialogue: 0,1:13:43.60,1:13:54.77,Default,,0,0,0,,test this out in the class today and prove it. It's a critical point. It's why the world can't\Nhandle the drug experience. It doesn't know what it is. What the person then is addicted to is the
Dialogue: 0,1:13:54.77,1:14:02.42,Default,,0,0,0,,re-experiencing of this energy field.\NDrugs block off the shadows, they block off the
Dialogue: 0,1:14:02.42,1:14:10.94,Default,,0,0,0,,clouds and allow you to experience a vibration\Nand energy field which is always there. But the drug itself does not have the power to create
Dialogue: 0,1:14:10.94,1:14:22.00,Default,,0,0,0,,that experience. It only has the power to remove the block to that experience,\Nthat experience which would be there all the time for everyone, all the time,
Dialogue: 0,1:14:22.00,1:14:28.06,Default,,0,0,0,,if it weren't for what's-in-the-box blocking our awareness of it.\NSo all the drugs
Dialogue: 0,1:14:28.06,1:14:36.70,Default,,0,0,0,,does is clear the field for you to experience something that is already\Nthere. It has no power to create that whatsoever. Drug has no power to create
Dialogue: 0,1:14:36.70,1:14:46.30,Default,,0,0,0,,any high at all. It only has the power to block off that which is not the truth\Nabout yourself and get closer to the energy and the feeling and the inner
Dialogue: 0,1:14:46.30,1:14:58.55,Default,,0,0,0,,vibration of that which is. That's why it is so addicting, see, because then the\Nleft brain says, the left brain gets that sequence. It gets to take the drug, move
Dialogue: 0,1:14:58.55,1:15:07.01,Default,,0,0,0,,up in the box, experience that feeling. It must be in the box. It must be in the\Ndrug. It must be in the drug. An aew person thinks it must be in the drug.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:07.01,1:15:19.26,Default,,0,0,0,,People, who in the great days of LSD, took LSD with proper preparation, you see.\NSpent a year of meditation and fasting and spiritual study, took it once, walked
Dialogue: 0,1:15:19.26,1:15:29.28,Default,,0,0,0,,out of that which they were and experienced that which was there since\Nthe beginning of time. They walked into that which always was.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:29.28,1:15:32.96,Default,,0,0,0,,. . .\Nand realized the truth of that, what that was, and never took it again.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:33.56,1:15:41.56,Default,,0,0,0,,People who really took LSD correctly took it maybe once, maximum twice.\NBecause it was very obvious that it wasn't a drug at all.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:41.76,1:15:49.64,Default,,0,0,0,,All the drug had done was remove your ability to witness that which is.\NAnd the realization of that which is then,
Dialogue: 0,1:15:50.18,1:15:58.62,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, the people came out of that with an intense spiritual commitment,\Nand you saw a great rise in spiritual commitment to spiritual values and all,
Dialogue: 0,1:15:58.62,1:16:07.80,Default,,0,0,0,,and then people spent the rest of their lives purifying themselves\Nto return to a state which only through the LSD experience,
Dialogue: 0,1:16:08.60,1:16:16.70,Default,,0,0,0,,let's say for them perhaps, did they verify the truth of that.\NSo the person suspected this is so, verified this is so,
Dialogue: 0,1:16:16.82,1:16:23.12,Default,,0,0,0,,and now spends the rest of their life returning to that.\NAnybody with any awareness realizes, obviously,
Dialogue: 0,1:16:23.34,1:16:28.98,Default,,0,0,0,,that you cannot experience the truth of that which you are by repeatedly taking LSD.\NI mean, that was sort of retarded.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:29.06,1:16:37.32,Default,,0,0,0,,That's not the right way to do it.\NAnybody who really took it in the proper context took it once.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:37.32,1:16:43.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Because all it did was verify for you that that is always there,\Nthat it is what it is,
Dialogue: 0,1:16:43.32,1:16:53.32,Default,,0,0,0,,and that you see that which is within you is blocking your awareness of that experience.\NThe work of removing that which is blocking the experience then
Dialogue: 0,1:16:53.32,1:16:57.32,Default,,0,0,0,,is what the rest of your life is dedicated to.\NSo that would be how to do it consciously.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:57.32,1:17:01.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Many people say,\Nwell, of course, did not do it consciously,
Dialogue: 0,1:17:01.51,1:17:07.51,Default,,0,0,0,,and instead for the glamour and the sensation of it.\NBut people who had a transcendental experience,
Dialogue: 0,1:17:07.51,1:17:13.51,Default,,0,0,0,,which happened in the very early days,\Nbecause it was then, in those days, considered a sacrament,
Dialogue: 0,1:17:13.51,1:17:19.51,Default,,0,0,0,,it allowed you, as Aldous Huxley said,\Nit opened the doors of perception,
Dialogue: 0,1:17:19.51,1:17:24.51,Default,,0,0,0,,allowed you to experience that which is.\NBut the drug does not create that which is.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:24.51,1:17:32.51,Default,,0,0,0,,And of course, that is one of the great problems in the drug experience,\Nis that the left brain begins to think that it is,
Dialogue: 0,1:17:32.51,1:17:37.80,Default,,0,0,0,,for the person who has never had that experience otherwise,\Nthat the power is in the drug.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:37.80,1:17:41.80,Default,,0,0,0,,The power is in the drug.\NThe person thinks the power is in the drug.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:41.80,1:17:47.25,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, in the beginning, a person, let's say, is nervous,\Nand self-conscious, and etc.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:47.25,1:17:51.25,Default,,0,0,0,,And they stop by, and they have two martinis,\Nand now they go into a mellow,
Dialogue: 0,1:17:51.25,1:17:55.25,Default,,0,0,0,,and they go to this business conference,\Nand they carry it out successfully.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:55.25,1:18:00.25,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, nobody is being harmed, right?\NThere's no scandal being created.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:00.25,1:18:05.25,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, what's wrong with that?\NWhat's wrong with moving from a negative energy field,
Dialogue: 0,1:18:05.25,1:18:10.25,Default,,0,0,0,,resentment, let's say, and nervousness, and anxiety,\Nand moving into a lovingness,
Dialogue: 0,1:18:10.25,1:18:15.92,Default,,0,0,0,,where you are concerned about the welfare of humanity,\Nand love, and generosity?
Dialogue: 0,1:18:15.92,1:18:19.92,Default,,0,0,0,,So what's wrong with that?\NWhy does it end up in such a disaster?
Dialogue: 0,1:18:19.92,1:18:27.53,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, how come it ends up in the pits of hell?\NHow does the energy field get reversed?
Dialogue: 0,1:18:27.53,1:18:31.53,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, why does it go from a positive,\Nmellow, happy lovingness,
Dialogue: 0,1:18:31.53,1:18:36.53,Default,,0,0,0,,to a hatefulness?\NThe father that used to have a drink or two on his way home,
Dialogue: 0,1:18:36.53,1:18:41.53,Default,,0,0,0,,and come home happy, and the kids love to see him,\Nnow as the years go by, comes home nasty,
Dialogue: 0,1:18:41.53,1:18:46.53,Default,,0,0,0,,and selfish, and then becomes physically violent,\Nand everybody hates him, and fears him,
Dialogue: 0,1:18:46.53,1:18:49.53,Default,,0,0,0,,and finally the family breaks up.\NWhat happened?
Dialogue: 0,1:18:49.53,1:18:53.72,Default,,0,0,0,,He's only doing the same thing he did in the beginning.\NIn the beginning he stopped for two martinis,
Dialogue: 0,1:18:53.72,1:18:56.72,Default,,0,0,0,,and he came home mellow.\NNow he stops for two martinis,
Dialogue: 0,1:18:56.72,1:18:59.75,Default,,0,0,0,,and he comes home violent and nasty.\NWhat has changed?
Dialogue: 0,1:18:59.75,1:19:02.75,Default,,0,0,0,,What has happened?\NWhat has been the critical?
Dialogue: 0,1:19:02.75,1:19:09.14,Default,,0,0,0,,What is going on?\NWhat's going on is that he's given the power to the drugs,
Dialogue: 0,1:19:09.14,1:19:15.49,Default,,0,0,0,,in my own particular research into the question.\NWhat's happened is that the energy field,
Dialogue: 0,1:19:15.49,1:19:20.65,Default,,0,0,0,,we said that the truth puts you above the line.\NIf truth puts you above the line,
Dialogue: 0,1:19:20.65,1:19:25.65,Default,,0,0,0,,then a lie puts you below the line.\NSo when he gives the power to the drug,
Dialogue: 0,1:19:25.65,1:19:31.84,Default,,0,0,0,,when he gives the power to the drug,\Nthen what happens is he reverses the energy field,
Dialogue: 0,1:19:31.84,1:19:39.38,Default,,0,0,0,,because the lie, the telling of the untruth,\Nis what reverses the field.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:39.38,1:19:43.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Now a lie that's told at a minus 50,\Nlet's say you're down in apathy at 50,
Dialogue: 0,1:19:43.38,1:19:47.38,Default,,0,0,0,,your life is one entire lie anyway.\NThe whole context of your life is a lie.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:47.38,1:19:52.38,Default,,0,0,0,,And all you do is lie all day long anyway,\Nso one more lie doesn't really have that profound an effect.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:52.38,1:19:57.21,Default,,0,0,0,,But if you're in a very high state,\Nand you owe the lie,
Dialogue: 0,1:19:57.21,1:20:01.21,Default,,0,0,0,,the effect is disastrous.\NA lie with a power of 550 behind it
Dialogue: 0,1:20:01.21,1:20:06.50,Default,,0,0,0,,is quite a different lie\Nthan a thought with an energy field of 50 behind it.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:06.50,1:20:11.50,Default,,0,0,0,,A lie at 550 has,\Ncan totally reverse all your energies
Dialogue: 0,1:20:11.50,1:20:16.50,Default,,0,0,0,,and totally transform your life now into destruction.\NSo we see,
Dialogue: 0,1:20:16.50,1:20:20.50,Default,,0,0,0,,it's the giving of the power,\Nthe power, the truth of that which you are,
Dialogue: 0,1:20:20.50,1:20:24.50,Default,,0,0,0,,you now deny,\Nand you say it does not exist within me.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:24.50,1:20:28.50,Default,,0,0,0,,On the contrary, it exists out there.\NIt is within that.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:28.50,1:20:33.50,Default,,0,0,0,,And the giving away the truth of that which you are\Nthen reverses the energy field.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:33.50,1:20:38.10,Default,,0,0,0,,And if you want, later we can test that out,\Ntest out the truth of that.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:38.10,1:20:42.10,Default,,0,0,0,,But it is the ascribing of the power,\Nthe truth of that which you are,
Dialogue: 0,1:20:42.10,1:20:47.10,Default,,0,0,0,,to something that is outside of you that you are not.\NAnd it is that statement
Dialogue: 0,1:20:47.10,1:20:52.10,Default,,0,0,0,,which is made in a high energy state.\NSee, it is in the high energy state that you say,
Dialogue: 0,1:20:52.10,1:20:56.26,Default,,0,0,0,,it is that that created this.\NYou didn't say that in a low energy state,
Dialogue: 0,1:20:56.26,1:21:00.26,Default,,0,0,0,,you said that in a high energy state.\NWith a lot of power.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:00.26,1:21:04.46,Default,,0,0,0,,550 is a lot of power.\NSo in a high energy state you said,
Dialogue: 0,1:21:04.46,1:21:08.46,Default,,0,0,0,,the power is in that.\NIt is that that I worship.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:08.46,1:21:12.46,Default,,0,0,0,,This is what I worship. It has become my idol.\NThis is the center of my life now.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:12.46,1:21:17.46,Default,,0,0,0,,God has been really replaced by that.\NThat which I am has been replaced by that.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:17.46,1:21:22.62,Default,,0,0,0,,The giving of the power away then to that\Nis what reverses the energy field.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:22.62,1:21:29.13,Default,,0,0,0,,So now, that which at one time you got high,\Nnow sends you into destruction.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:29.13,1:21:35.13,Default,,0,0,0,,The very same thing now is the two-faced genus.\NSuddenly its face turns around
Dialogue: 0,1:21:35.13,1:21:42.13,Default,,0,0,0,,and you see that the energy field has reversed.\NThat which once was positive in your life
Dialogue: 0,1:21:42.13,1:21:47.80,Default,,0,0,0,,is now the most destructive thing in your life.\NSo I thought, well, we'll take a break now
Dialogue: 0,1:21:47.80,1:21:53.80,Default,,0,0,0,,that we've gotten to what the addiction is.\NThe addiction is to that state of consciousness called bliss.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:53.80,1:21:59.80,Default,,0,0,0,,It really has nothing at all to do with the drug.\NAnd the drug comes in accidentally in our society,
Dialogue: 0,1:21:59.80,1:22:04.80,Default,,0,0,0,,because most people don't meditate themselves\Nin the states of samadhi.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:04.80,1:22:09.80,Default,,0,0,0,,They experience that state only through drugs.\NAnd therefore it is a phenomenon of our society
Dialogue: 0,1:22:09.80,1:22:14.93,Default,,0,0,0,,of being a materialistic culture.\NI said this afternoon we'll test out,
Dialogue: 0,1:22:14.93,1:22:21.93,Default,,0,0,0,,we'll use, for instance, kinesiology\Nto test out the truth of some of the statements we've made.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:21.93,1:22:27.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Especially, and most importantly,\Nthe one that people who themselves have become addicted
Dialogue: 0,1:22:27.93,1:22:34.82,Default,,0,0,0,,are most impressed by,\Nis the awareness of what it is they're addicted to.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:34.82,1:22:42.82,Default,,0,0,0,,After saying this for some time, a year or two,\NI ran across a writing by Ramana Maharshi.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:42.82,1:22:48.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Ramana Maharshi being one of the great saints of India,\Nenlightened in the view of the world,
Dialogue: 0,1:22:48.02,1:22:56.17,Default,,0,0,0,,and a very famous person.\NBut anyway, Ramana Maharshi said,
Dialogue: 0,1:22:56.17,1:23:02.84,Default,,0,0,0,,in one of his books that I ran across,\Nthat the reason the person becomes intoxicated
Dialogue: 0,1:23:02.84,1:23:10.19,Default,,0,0,0,,is to experience the self.\NAnd that once a person learns what it is they are seeking
Dialogue: 0,1:23:10.19,1:23:15.19,Default,,0,0,0,,through the intoxication,\Nthey will then seek that directly.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:15.19,1:23:20.19,Default,,0,0,0,,So I thought it was very interesting,\Nbecause Ramana Maharshi never took a drink in his life.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:20.19,1:23:24.80,Default,,0,0,0,,He knew nothing about addiction,\Nand yet he knew that.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:24.80,1:23:32.18,Default,,0,0,0,,That once the person realizes what it is they are seeking,\Nthat inner experience in consciousness,
Dialogue: 0,1:23:32.18,1:23:37.18,Default,,0,0,0,,once they realize what that is,\Nthey will then begin to seek it directly.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:37.18,1:23:46.11,Default,,0,0,0,,And of course, that's the whole function of 12-step groups.\NThat's the whole function of Alcoholics Anonymous.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:46.11,1:23:51.14,Default,,0,0,0,,So now we can see,\Nfrom a viewpoint of consciousness itself,
Dialogue: 0,1:23:51.14,1:23:57.24,Default,,0,0,0,,we have some greater understanding then,\Nof how the 12 steps work,
Dialogue: 0,1:23:57.24,1:24:04.24,Default,,0,0,0,,and how the whole field, the energy field, of AA works.\NBecause we see in the first step,
Dialogue: 0,1:24:04.24,1:24:09.24,Default,,0,0,0,,the first step was we admitted we were powerless.\NWe admitted we were powerless,
Dialogue: 0,1:24:09.24,1:24:13.34,Default,,0,0,0,,powerless over alcohol or drugs,\Nas the case may be.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:13.34,1:24:16.53,Default,,0,0,0,,And the minute,\Nwhen you come out of denial,
Dialogue: 0,1:24:16.53,1:24:20.53,Default,,0,0,0,,when you come out of this denial,\Nand the reversed energy field,
Dialogue: 0,1:24:20.53,1:24:25.98,Default,,0,0,0,,which is bringing destruction into the person's life,\Nthe admission that I'm powerless over alcohol or drugs
Dialogue: 0,1:24:25.98,1:24:31.01,Default,,0,0,0,,is the first statement of the truth.\NAnd what it does is reverse the energy field
Dialogue: 0,1:24:31.01,1:24:35.04,Default,,0,0,0,,and bring into the person's life,\Nthrough empowerment,
Dialogue: 0,1:24:35.04,1:24:41.04,Default,,0,0,0,,the first reaction you see,\Nin fact, the external representation of that empowerment,
Dialogue: 0,1:24:41.04,1:24:48.78,Default,,0,0,0,,is that they find themselves now in an energy field of 500 and over.\NSo they become empowered then.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:48.78,1:24:52.78,Default,,0,0,0,,So the first step of Alcoholics Anonymous then,\Nbecause it tells the truth,
Dialogue: 0,1:24:52.78,1:24:58.42,Default,,0,0,0,,reverses the energy field, the admission,\Nthat I'm powerless over drugs and alcohol.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:58.42,1:25:04.58,Default,,0,0,0,,The second step of Alcoholics Anonymous then,\Nyou know, deepens that statement of truth.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:04.58,1:25:08.58,Default,,0,0,0,,The awareness that some power\Ngreater than myself
Dialogue: 0,1:25:08.58,1:25:13.70,Default,,0,0,0,,is necessary to return me to sanity.\NInsanity, in that definition,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:13.70,1:25:20.70,Default,,0,0,0,,being anything in these destructive energy states,\Nthose denials of the truth then,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:20.70,1:25:27.70,Default,,0,0,0,,and languaged as insanity.\NSomething greater than myself is necessary
Dialogue: 0,1:25:27.70,1:25:32.70,Default,,0,0,0,,to turn this whole field around.\NSomething greater than myself,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:32.70,1:25:37.70,Default,,0,0,0,,and by that they're talking about the small self.\NSomething outside of,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:37.70,1:25:43.96,Default,,0,0,0,,and more powerful than the ego,\Nis going to be necessary to conquer the ego.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:43.96,1:25:51.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Something greater than what is in the box.\NSomething that is outside of the box.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:51.50,1:25:55.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Some lever that has the power\Nto lift that which is in the box.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:55.50,1:26:01.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Intuitive awareness that I, of my own self,\Nthis self here, unaided,
Dialogue: 0,1:26:01.50,1:26:07.50,Default,,0,0,0,,do then have the power to overcome\Nthe attraction of an energy field of that power.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:07.50,1:26:14.50,Default,,0,0,0,,The attraction to return to that state of consciousness\Nis so powerful that it requires something
Dialogue: 0,1:26:14.50,1:26:20.50,Default,,0,0,0,,of equal power to neutralize it and to handle it.\NThat's an admission of the truth.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:20.50,1:26:27.81,Default,,0,0,0,,So the second step then,\Nfurthers and deepens the commitment to the truth
Dialogue: 0,1:26:27.81,1:26:34.77,Default,,0,0,0,,and brings the person face to face with the third step.\NThe willingness to turn over
Dialogue: 0,1:26:34.77,1:26:39.77,Default,,0,0,0,,my life and my will\Nto God as I understand him,
Dialogue: 0,1:26:39.77,1:26:43.77,Default,,0,0,0,,to something greater than myself.\NThe turning over,
Dialogue: 0,1:26:43.77,1:26:48.15,Default,,0,0,0,,the surrender.\NSo the step of surrender then,
Dialogue: 0,1:26:48.15,1:26:53.41,Default,,0,0,0,,coming out of the pain and the suffering\Nof the descents into hell,
Dialogue: 0,1:26:53.41,1:26:58.53,Default,,0,0,0,,because these lower states are really\Napproaching states of hell.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:58.53,1:27:03.53,Default,,0,0,0,,The surrender, the letting go then,\Nand the turning over of one's life
Dialogue: 0,1:27:03.53,1:27:08.53,Default,,0,0,0,,to something greater than oneself,\Nthat moves one up into this energy field
Dialogue: 0,1:27:08.53,1:27:15.17,Default,,0,0,0,,of the self-help groups of the 500 energy fields.\NThat surrender, that I myself cannot do it,
Dialogue: 0,1:27:15.17,1:27:20.17,Default,,0,0,0,,is what brings about eventually the salvation\Nbecause it opens the space for something
Dialogue: 0,1:27:20.17,1:27:24.17,Default,,0,0,0,,greater than oneself to come in.\NIt opens the space for the grace of God.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:24.17,1:27:31.52,Default,,0,0,0,,And so people who recover from the addictions\Nwill say that it happened to them
Dialogue: 0,1:27:31.52,1:27:35.52,Default,,0,0,0,,as the grace of God.\NIt is not something that the ego did
Dialogue: 0,1:27:35.52,1:27:39.52,Default,,0,0,0,,of its own doingness.\NThat it was something outside
Dialogue: 0,1:27:39.52,1:27:43.52,Default,,0,0,0,,of that which I thought I was\Nthat transformed my life
Dialogue: 0,1:27:43.52,1:27:47.52,Default,,0,0,0,,and the desire to drink disappeared,\Nwhich is what exactly happened
Dialogue: 0,1:27:47.52,1:27:51.52,Default,,0,0,0,,to my own personal experience.\NBeing an atheist at the time,
Dialogue: 0,1:27:51.52,1:27:55.65,Default,,0,0,0,,an atheist for some 20 years,\Nand a devoted atheist,
Dialogue: 0,1:27:55.65,1:27:59.65,Default,,0,0,0,,a devout atheist,\Nnot a casual cocktail lounge atheist,
Dialogue: 0,1:27:59.65,1:28:03.68,Default,,0,0,0,,but I mean I was an atheist,\Nbecause I was committed to the truth.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:03.68,1:28:08.87,Default,,0,0,0,,And we'll get to that when we talk about\Nthe various conceptualizations of God.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:08.87,1:28:15.32,Default,,0,0,0,,My own dedication to the truth told me\Nthat how it was conceived was false.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:15.32,1:28:19.32,Default,,0,0,0,,And so anyway,\Nthat preoccupation with God
Dialogue: 0,1:28:19.32,1:28:23.32,Default,,0,0,0,,has gone on throughout my life.\NWhen I was a child,
Dialogue: 0,1:28:23.32,1:28:28.32,Default,,0,0,0,,I was a devoted religionist.\NAnd then I became a devoted atheist.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:28.32,1:28:32.35,Default,,0,0,0,,And then in a moment\Nwhen I myself hit bottom
Dialogue: 0,1:28:32.35,1:28:37.35,Default,,0,0,0,,at a great depth and great despair\Nand out of utter hopelessness,
Dialogue: 0,1:28:37.35,1:28:41.64,Default,,0,0,0,,I asked God,\Nif there was such an entity
Dialogue: 0,1:28:41.64,1:28:45.86,Default,,0,0,0,,in the universe to help me.\NI didn't hold my breath,
Dialogue: 0,1:28:45.86,1:28:49.86,Default,,0,0,0,,not thinking that there was any such item.\NSo the denial broke down,
Dialogue: 0,1:28:49.86,1:28:53.86,Default,,0,0,0,,the arrogance of the intellect.\NThe arrogance of the intellect.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:53.86,1:28:57.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Being a left-brained person,\NI didn't conceive that there was anything
Dialogue: 0,1:28:57.86,1:29:02.86,Default,,0,0,0,,other than intelligence.\NI thought that intelligence was God,
Dialogue: 0,1:29:02.86,1:29:06.86,Default,,0,0,0,,that man through his intelligence\Nwould solve all his problems,
Dialogue: 0,1:29:06.86,1:29:10.86,Default,,0,0,0,,through his intellect.\NAnd I worshipped the intellect.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:10.86,1:29:14.86,Default,,0,0,0,,I was baptized by the God of the intellect.\NReason, you know, Thomas Paine's age,
Dialogue: 0,1:29:14.86,1:29:19.27,Default,,0,0,0,,reason really hit me when I was like 15 or 16\Nwhen I became an atheist.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:19.27,1:29:23.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Reason and the intellect,\Nthe left brain, the intellect,
Dialogue: 0,1:29:23.27,1:29:27.62,Default,,0,0,0,,the IQ, I was born with a good IQ.\NSo I thought IQ,
Dialogue: 0,1:29:27.62,1:29:31.62,Default,,0,0,0,,intelligence, reason, science,\Nthat was going to solve all man's dilemmas.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:31.62,1:29:36.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Hmm.\NFollowing my best reasoning,
Dialogue: 0,1:29:36.30,1:29:40.30,Default,,0,0,0,,I found myself at death's door,\Nhaving been given up as hopeless.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:40.30,1:29:44.30,Default,,0,0,0,,And so, having followed my own best reasoning,\NI found myself
Dialogue: 0,1:29:44.30,1:29:48.30,Default,,0,0,0,,at the very bottom of the box,\Nvery close to death.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:48.30,1:29:53.26,Default,,0,0,0,,And suicide, by the way,\Ncalibrates at a minus 50.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:53.26,1:29:57.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Zero, it's below zero,\Nit's in the lower beginnings of hell.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:57.38,1:30:01.90,Default,,0,0,0,,So I had a reversed energy field of minus 50.\NSo from that state,
Dialogue: 0,1:30:01.90,1:30:05.90,Default,,0,0,0,,the atheist asked if there was something\Ngreater than himself in the universe
Dialogue: 0,1:30:05.90,1:30:10.02,Default,,0,0,0,,and totally surrendered\Nand committed himself to that.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:10.02,1:30:14.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Whatever there was.\NThat emptiness, it seemed to me that nothingness.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:14.02,1:30:18.54,Default,,0,0,0,,And walked off the cliff.\NAnd in that instant,
Dialogue: 0,1:30:18.54,1:30:22.54,Default,,0,0,0,,in that instant,\Nwas an enormous transformation.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:22.54,1:30:26.54,Default,,0,0,0,,And the person that had been\Nno longer existed.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:26.54,1:30:30.82,Default,,0,0,0,,And instead,\Nstood in the presence of the infinite,
Dialogue: 0,1:30:30.82,1:30:34.82,Default,,0,0,0,,the infiniteness of the universe.\NThat which had infinite power.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:34.82,1:30:39.59,Default,,0,0,0,,And it ran me.\NIt ran whatever this body did
Dialogue: 0,1:30:39.59,1:30:43.72,Default,,0,0,0,,or whatever it said,\Nwhat it thought, what went on with it,
Dialogue: 0,1:30:43.72,1:30:47.78,Default,,0,0,0,,was run by that\Ninfinite presence.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:47.78,1:30:51.88,Default,,0,0,0,,So from the very bottom of the box,\Nyou can break out of the box
Dialogue: 0,1:30:51.88,1:30:55.88,Default,,0,0,0,,through that\Nexperience of surrender.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:55.88,1:30:59.98,Default,,0,0,0,,So that's the third step,\Nwhich creates the space
Dialogue: 0,1:30:59.98,1:31:03.98,Default,,0,0,0,,for that which by grace\Ntakes the place of that which we were.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:03.98,1:31:15.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Got a question?\NWhat she asks is,
Dialogue: 0,1:31:15.69,1:31:19.69,Default,,0,0,0,,is grace available to anyone who asks for it?\NIt is only by asking for it
Dialogue: 0,1:31:19.69,1:31:24.01,Default,,0,0,0,,that we create the space.\NIt is because of the law of free will.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:24.01,1:31:28.33,Default,,0,0,0,,So when we ask for it,\Nwe create the space,
Dialogue: 0,1:31:28.33,1:31:32.33,Default,,0,0,0,,the possibility\Nfor it to happen.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:32.33,1:31:36.33,Default,,0,0,0,,It was only through the surrender\Nthat such an incredible experience
Dialogue: 0,1:31:36.33,1:31:41.32,Default,,0,0,0,,could have occurred.\NBill Wilson said that
Dialogue: 0,1:31:41.32,1:31:45.32,Default,,0,0,0,,AA is the language of the heart.\NAA is the language of the heart.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:45.32,1:31:50.28,Default,,0,0,0,,That heart being.\NSo when we talk about that chakra,
Dialogue: 0,1:31:50.28,1:31:54.28,Default,,0,0,0,,the energy field of the heart,\Nsee these are the laws
Dialogue: 0,1:31:54.28,1:31:58.28,Default,,0,0,0,,of the lower energy fields,\Nthe lower chakras,
Dialogue: 0,1:31:58.28,1:32:02.31,Default,,0,0,0,,you move up through the solar plexus\Nand then you move into the heart.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:02.31,1:32:06.31,Default,,0,0,0,,So Bill Wilson said AA\Nis the language of the heart,
Dialogue: 0,1:32:06.31,1:32:10.92,Default,,0,0,0,,not of the intellect,\Nnot of the head,
Dialogue: 0,1:32:10.92,1:32:15.66,Default,,0,0,0,,not of the mind with a small m,\Nbut that of one's own inner experience.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:15.66,1:32:19.66,Default,,0,0,0,,So the third step then opens\Nthe way for that.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:19.66,1:32:23.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Through that despair,\Nthe arrogance of the ego
Dialogue: 0,1:32:23.69,1:32:27.69,Default,,0,0,0,,finally lets go.\NThrough the addiction,
Dialogue: 0,1:32:27.69,1:32:31.72,Default,,0,0,0,,there is a total transformation.\NThe transformation may not be complete
Dialogue: 0,1:32:31.72,1:32:35.72,Default,,0,0,0,,and include the whole personality,\Nobviously,
Dialogue: 0,1:32:35.72,1:32:39.72,Default,,0,0,0,,because that's the reason for the 12 steps.\NBut at least in one area
Dialogue: 0,1:32:39.72,1:32:43.72,Default,,0,0,0,,there has been complete and absolute\Nand total surrender
Dialogue: 0,1:32:43.72,1:32:48.39,Default,,0,0,0,,and its replacement by grace.\NThe fourth step then says
Dialogue: 0,1:32:48.39,1:32:52.39,Default,,0,0,0,,that we took a fearless moral inventory.\NSo the fourth step then says
Dialogue: 0,1:32:52.39,1:32:56.39,Default,,0,0,0,,what we did was we looked in the box,\Nwe looked in our box
Dialogue: 0,1:32:56.39,1:33:01.22,Default,,0,0,0,,in our own particular case.\NAnd after looking in the box
Dialogue: 0,1:33:01.22,1:33:05.22,Default,,0,0,0,,to see what's in there in our own particular case,\Nfor one thing we discovered
Dialogue: 0,1:33:05.22,1:33:09.22,Default,,0,0,0,,if we move on to the fifth step\Nthat what's in our box is no different
Dialogue: 0,1:33:09.22,1:33:13.38,Default,,0,0,0,,than what's in everybody else's box,\Nthe ego being the same in everyone.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:13.38,1:33:17.38,Default,,0,0,0,,The ego is really the same\Nin its design, in its overall
Dialogue: 0,1:33:17.38,1:33:21.38,Default,,0,0,0,,way of being in everyone.\NSo that whatever we find within our own
Dialogue: 0,1:33:21.38,1:33:25.38,Default,,0,0,0,,personal experience really falls\Nsomewhere within the box.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:25.38,1:33:29.74,Default,,0,0,0,,And therefore the fifth step\Nsays we admitted
Dialogue: 0,1:33:29.74,1:33:33.74,Default,,0,0,0,,to God and to ourselves\Nand to another human
Dialogue: 0,1:33:33.74,1:33:37.77,Default,,0,0,0,,being the exact\Nnature of what we discovered
Dialogue: 0,1:33:37.77,1:33:42.12,Default,,0,0,0,,within ourself.\NIn admitting it to
Dialogue: 0,1:33:42.12,1:33:46.12,Default,,0,0,0,,myself, in admitting it\Nto God and to another fellow human being
Dialogue: 0,1:33:46.12,1:33:50.12,Default,,0,0,0,,what I've done now is reversed the\Nenergy field on it, taken the charge
Dialogue: 0,1:33:50.12,1:33:54.41,Default,,0,0,0,,off it, removed its\Npower to corrode and
Dialogue: 0,1:33:54.41,1:33:58.70,Default,,0,0,0,,destroy. When I look\Nat a thing, when I let go of the deny
Dialogue: 0,1:33:58.70,1:34:02.70,Default,,0,0,0,,when I'm willing to handle whatever\Npain comes up in the looking at it,
Dialogue: 0,1:34:02.70,1:34:07.11,Default,,0,0,0,,the willingness to heal it,\Nto ask that it be healed,
Dialogue: 0,1:34:07.11,1:34:11.11,Default,,0,0,0,,to share it with another human being\Nis part of the whole process
Dialogue: 0,1:34:11.11,1:34:15.30,Default,,0,0,0,,of healing it.\NBecause that which is held in mind
Dialogue: 0,1:34:15.30,1:34:19.30,Default,,0,0,0,,and never shared has by\Nthat virtue of that power
Dialogue: 0,1:34:19.30,1:34:23.53,Default,,0,0,0,,to corrode. The minute it's shared\Nwith another human being it's now held
Dialogue: 0,1:34:23.53,1:34:27.53,Default,,0,0,0,,in a different way, it's held in a different\Ncontext, it's transformed into a shared
Dialogue: 0,1:34:27.53,1:34:31.72,Default,,0,0,0,,communication and\Nits capacity to destroy has not
Dialogue: 0,1:34:31.72,1:34:35.72,Default,,0,0,0,,been removed. So the event\Nin one's life, instead
Dialogue: 0,1:34:35.72,1:34:39.72,Default,,0,0,0,,of lying awake at night\Nhating in self-hatred, that
Dialogue: 0,1:34:39.72,1:34:43.72,Default,,0,0,0,,self-hatred which comes out the bottom\Nof the box, maybe
Dialogue: 0,1:34:43.72,1:34:47.72,Default,,0,0,0,,what's left of it is a mild\Nregret, a mild regret.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:47.72,1:34:53.61,Default,,0,0,0,,So that's what Bill Wilson said.\NHe said that whatever you've done in your life
Dialogue: 0,1:34:53.61,1:34:57.90,Default,,0,0,0,,at best, the way to hold\Nit now is with a decent regret.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:57.90,1:35:01.99,Default,,0,0,0,,A decent regret.\NTo replace that horrible
Dialogue: 0,1:35:01.99,1:35:05.99,Default,,0,0,0,,intense self-hatred and depression\Nand contempt, self-contempt
Dialogue: 0,1:35:05.99,1:35:09.99,Default,,0,0,0,,which leads to the actual\Nseeking out of destruction.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:09.99,1:35:14.02,Default,,0,0,0,,You see that the process coming out of the box\Nis the
Dialogue: 0,1:35:14.02,1:35:18.02,Default,,0,0,0,,willful, lethal satisfaction\Nout of one's own
Dialogue: 0,1:35:18.02,1:35:22.02,Default,,0,0,0,,destruction. Because an energy\Nfuel that reverses now seeks
Dialogue: 0,1:35:22.02,1:35:26.18,Default,,0,0,0,,its own destruction. And so\Nyou tell the person that they're killing
Dialogue: 0,1:35:26.18,1:35:30.18,Default,,0,0,0,,themselves with drugs\Nand you think you're going to scare them out of it
Dialogue: 0,1:35:30.18,1:35:34.18,Default,,0,0,0,,you're merely appealing to this.\NYou bet I am. Love it.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:34.18,1:35:38.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Love it. Love it.\NSo you see how you're playing right
Dialogue: 0,1:35:38.28,1:35:42.28,Default,,0,0,0,,into the person's self-destruction.\NTo say if you keep on drinking
Dialogue: 0,1:35:42.28,1:35:46.28,Default,,0,0,0,,your liver is going to fail.\NFine. The people
Dialogue: 0,1:35:46.28,1:35:50.60,Default,,0,0,0,,got an unconscious satisfaction\Nout of that
Dialogue: 0,1:35:50.60,1:35:54.60,Default,,0,0,0,,self-destruction. There was a purpose in it\Nand it was the only way they could see to go.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:54.60,1:35:58.60,Default,,0,0,0,,In this energy field here\Nself-destruction is obviously
Dialogue: 0,1:35:58.60,1:36:02.60,Default,,0,0,0,,what is appealing to you and attractive.\NSo, the fifth step
Dialogue: 0,1:36:02.60,1:36:06.60,Default,,0,0,0,,then removes the appeal and the\Nattractiveness of that which is
Dialogue: 0,1:36:06.60,1:36:10.73,Default,,0,0,0,,destructive. It is no longer\Nappealing.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:10.73,1:36:14.92,Default,,0,0,0,,That leads us to the sixth through\Nthe ninth steps, you see.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:14.92,1:36:18.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Having looked at what's in the\Nbox and having seen what its
Dialogue: 0,1:36:18.92,1:36:22.92,Default,,0,0,0,,nature is now and admitted\Nit to ourself and changed the charge
Dialogue: 0,1:36:22.92,1:36:26.92,Default,,0,0,0,,on that through sharing\Nit and asking God's forgiveness
Dialogue: 0,1:36:26.92,1:36:31.27,Default,,0,0,0,,and help with it. Then what we\Ndo is we move back into the world
Dialogue: 0,1:36:31.27,1:36:35.27,Default,,0,0,0,,into a step of action. We\Nmoved up in the box to appropriate
Dialogue: 0,1:36:35.27,1:36:39.27,Default,,0,0,0,,action and not through action\Nto try and undo what damage
Dialogue: 0,1:36:39.27,1:36:43.27,Default,,0,0,0,,we can. To repair\Nwhatever fences that we
Dialogue: 0,1:36:43.27,1:36:47.27,Default,,0,0,0,,can repair. To\Ntell people that we're sorry for how we
Dialogue: 0,1:36:47.27,1:36:51.27,Default,,0,0,0,,were. To\Nask for their forgiveness. To
Dialogue: 0,1:36:51.27,1:36:56.07,Default,,0,0,0,,pay up the bills that we didn't pay.\NYou know, to give
Dialogue: 0,1:36:56.07,1:37:00.30,Default,,0,0,0,,the employer a good day's work.\NAnd we always suggest that people
Dialogue: 0,1:37:00.30,1:37:04.30,Default,,0,0,0,,do that with the help of a sponsor.\NHopefully that their wisdom will keep
Dialogue: 0,1:37:04.30,1:37:08.62,Default,,0,0,0,,people from impetuously\Nacting out in a self-destructive
Dialogue: 0,1:37:08.62,1:37:12.62,Default,,0,0,0,,way. But the best way\Nto repay your boss
Dialogue: 0,1:37:12.62,1:37:16.62,Default,,0,0,0,,is not to tell them that you've been\Nembezzling
Dialogue: 0,1:37:16.62,1:37:20.62,Default,,0,0,0,,out of the cash box the last ten years, which\Nmake it an M.I.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:20.62,1:37:24.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Raider calling the police.\NThe best way to repay him would be to give him
Dialogue: 0,1:37:24.62,1:37:28.62,Default,,0,0,0,,an honest day's work for a change.\NAnd the best
Dialogue: 0,1:37:28.62,1:37:32.62,Default,,0,0,0,,way to heal and repair\Nyour relationship is to put
Dialogue: 0,1:37:32.62,1:37:37.16,Default,,0,0,0,,the best that you can into it to make that\Nrelationship work. So to try
Dialogue: 0,1:37:37.16,1:37:41.16,Default,,0,0,0,,to undo the damage that came out of\Nthe past then. So that
Dialogue: 0,1:37:41.16,1:37:45.16,Default,,0,0,0,,that inner searching into\Nwhat was wrong within then
Dialogue: 0,1:37:45.16,1:37:50.57,Default,,0,0,0,,becomes reflected back in the world\Nin those steps six through nine.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:50.57,1:37:54.57,Default,,0,0,0,,The tenth step then says\Nthat we began to, we
Dialogue: 0,1:37:54.57,1:37:58.57,Default,,0,0,0,,made a habit of this. In other words,\Nit became our way of life.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:58.57,1:38:02.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Self-purification.\NBecause the drugs took us to the bottom of
Dialogue: 0,1:38:02.57,1:38:06.57,Default,,0,0,0,,the box and now through the\Nspiritual program of the
Dialogue: 0,1:38:06.57,1:38:10.66,Default,,0,0,0,,twelve steps we're moving back up through the\Nbox. So the tenth step said
Dialogue: 0,1:38:10.66,1:38:14.66,Default,,0,0,0,,that this became our way of life.\NIt is the way we became in
Dialogue: 0,1:38:14.66,1:38:19.05,Default,,0,0,0,,the world. That the best of\Nour knowledge as we became aware
Dialogue: 0,1:38:19.05,1:38:23.05,Default,,0,0,0,,as we became aware\Nof that which was wrong within us
Dialogue: 0,1:38:23.05,1:38:27.05,Default,,0,0,0,,we sought to correct it.\NAnd so that commitment to self-correction
Dialogue: 0,1:38:27.05,1:38:31.05,Default,,0,0,0,,to spiritual growth\Nto becoming more conscious then
Dialogue: 0,1:38:31.05,1:38:35.05,Default,,0,0,0,,becomes part of the way of life\Nthat comes out of this experience.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:35.05,1:38:40.20,Default,,0,0,0,,The eleventh step\Nis an interesting one. The eleventh
Dialogue: 0,1:38:40.20,1:38:44.81,Default,,0,0,0,,step says, sought through\Nprayer and meditation
Dialogue: 0,1:38:44.81,1:38:48.81,Default,,0,0,0,,to increase our conscious contact\Nwith God as we understood Him.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:48.81,1:38:52.81,Default,,0,0,0,,That's a very interesting statement\Nwhen you look at it. It says
Dialogue: 0,1:38:52.81,1:38:57.10,Default,,0,0,0,,sought through prayer and meditation\Nto increase
Dialogue: 0,1:38:57.10,1:39:01.10,Default,,0,0,0,,our conscious contact with God.\NTo increase our contact with
Dialogue: 0,1:39:01.10,1:39:05.19,Default,,0,0,0,,God as we understood Him.\NSo what that is saying then is
Dialogue: 0,1:39:05.19,1:39:09.19,Default,,0,0,0,,by the time you've gone through\Nsteps one through ten
Dialogue: 0,1:39:09.19,1:39:13.19,Default,,0,0,0,,eleven doesn't say try to\Nestablish contact with some
Dialogue: 0,1:39:13.19,1:39:17.19,Default,,0,0,0,,power greater than myself.\NEleven says increase
Dialogue: 0,1:39:17.19,1:39:21.35,Default,,0,0,0,,that which has already happened.\NSo that
Dialogue: 0,1:39:21.35,1:39:25.35,Default,,0,0,0,,whole process of surrender\Nthe opening of the energy fuels
Dialogue: 0,1:39:25.35,1:39:29.74,Default,,0,0,0,,the experience of some\Ninner grace, the spiritual
Dialogue: 0,1:39:29.74,1:39:33.74,Default,,0,0,0,,growth that comes out of that\Nwhat happens is you reconnect within yourself
Dialogue: 0,1:39:33.74,1:39:37.74,Default,,0,0,0,,with something that is rock\Nlike. See that which is love
Dialogue: 0,1:39:37.74,1:39:41.74,Default,,0,0,0,,that which is divine\Nis not different than love.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:41.74,1:39:45.77,Default,,0,0,0,,So\NI always tell people
Dialogue: 0,1:39:45.77,1:39:49.77,Default,,0,0,0,,in these programs who\Nhave trouble with the God aspect
Dialogue: 0,1:39:49.77,1:39:53.77,Default,,0,0,0,,of it to forget about the God aspect\Nof it and instead commit themselves
Dialogue: 0,1:39:53.77,1:39:57.77,Default,,0,0,0,,to this energy fuel called\Nlove and to these states up here
Dialogue: 0,1:39:57.77,1:40:02.73,Default,,0,0,0,,which are called compassion\Nto commit oneself to truth
Dialogue: 0,1:40:02.73,1:40:06.76,Default,,0,0,0,,to love and to compassion.\NForget about the God aspect
Dialogue: 0,1:40:06.76,1:40:10.76,Default,,0,0,0,,because what happens as time goes\Non is you feel that
Dialogue: 0,1:40:10.76,1:40:14.76,Default,,0,0,0,,rock like interconnectedness\Nand so you'll hear people
Dialogue: 0,1:40:14.76,1:40:18.95,Default,,0,0,0,,who have been sober for some time\Nwill talk about their sobriety
Dialogue: 0,1:40:18.95,1:40:23.30,Default,,0,0,0,,as though it was some very\Nwonderful and positive
Dialogue: 0,1:40:23.30,1:40:27.43,Default,,0,0,0,,attribute\Nand they will guard that with their life.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:27.43,1:40:31.43,Default,,0,0,0,,What these people seemed to have\Nwas something that was so great
Dialogue: 0,1:40:31.43,1:40:35.43,Default,,0,0,0,,that they would go to any lengths to guard it\Nand to protect it. Something of
Dialogue: 0,1:40:35.43,1:40:39.43,Default,,0,0,0,,great significance that they had something\Nover and beyond that which they had gotten out of
Dialogue: 0,1:40:39.43,1:40:43.43,Default,,0,0,0,,alcohol and drugs in the first place\Notherwise they would still be back in alcohol
Dialogue: 0,1:40:43.43,1:40:47.43,Default,,0,0,0,,and drugs. Something of a greater\Ndimension had come into their life
Dialogue: 0,1:40:47.43,1:40:51.50,Default,,0,0,0,,and it was within them.\NThe kingdom of God is experienced
Dialogue: 0,1:40:51.50,1:40:55.78,Default,,0,0,0,,within and so that\Nrock like reconnection with that which
Dialogue: 0,1:40:55.78,1:40:59.78,Default,,0,0,0,,they had sought in the beginning\Nnow was happening. So step 11
Dialogue: 0,1:40:59.78,1:41:03.85,Default,,0,0,0,,then merely said\Nthat there was a desire
Dialogue: 0,1:41:03.85,1:41:07.85,Default,,0,0,0,,now and following through\Non how to increase the power of that
Dialogue: 0,1:41:07.85,1:41:11.85,Default,,0,0,0,,connectedness with something that\Nhad come back within the self.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:11.85,1:41:16.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Some re-experiencing of truth\Nhad recurred
Dialogue: 0,1:41:16.17,1:41:20.17,Default,,0,0,0,,and that brought them to the 12th step\Nand the 12th step then explains
Dialogue: 0,1:41:20.17,1:41:24.17,Default,,0,0,0,,what the whole process\Nof addiction is about.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:24.17,1:41:28.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Step 12 says\Nhaving become conscious as a result
Dialogue: 0,1:41:28.17,1:41:32.17,Default,,0,0,0,,of this total addictive experience\Nof having become addicted, having
Dialogue: 0,1:41:32.17,1:41:36.17,Default,,0,0,0,,surrendered, having hit bottom\Nhaving turned around, having
Dialogue: 0,1:41:36.17,1:41:40.97,Default,,0,0,0,,gone through a process of spiritual purification\Nand the wording of it
Dialogue: 0,1:41:40.97,1:41:44.97,Default,,0,0,0,,is having had a spiritual\Nawakening as a result
Dialogue: 0,1:41:44.97,1:41:49.64,Default,,0,0,0,,of this whole experience.\NSo now we see what the process
Dialogue: 0,1:41:49.64,1:41:53.64,Default,,0,0,0,,of addiction is all about. It is a\Nmovement in consciousness
Dialogue: 0,1:41:53.64,1:41:57.64,Default,,0,0,0,,it is a one way street\Na one way commitment because
Dialogue: 0,1:41:57.64,1:42:01.64,Default,,0,0,0,,once your own consciousness\Nhas picked addiction as
Dialogue: 0,1:42:01.64,1:42:05.64,Default,,0,0,0,,the way to becoming conscious\Nas the way to becoming spiritually aware
Dialogue: 0,1:42:05.64,1:42:09.64,Default,,0,0,0,,there is no backing up\Nthere is no changing of one's mind
Dialogue: 0,1:42:09.64,1:42:13.74,Default,,0,0,0,,you cannot join this pathway\Nand then leave it and join some other pathway
Dialogue: 0,1:42:13.74,1:42:18.25,Default,,0,0,0,,and commit to some other church\Nand then go to unity for a while
Dialogue: 0,1:42:18.25,1:42:22.25,Default,,0,0,0,,and then do the course of miracles\Nmove around through one thing and another
Dialogue: 0,1:42:22.25,1:42:26.25,Default,,0,0,0,,you are now committed\Nto a one way street
Dialogue: 0,1:42:26.25,1:42:30.60,Default,,0,0,0,,walking a razor's edge because\Nthere isn't enough room on it
Dialogue: 0,1:42:30.60,1:42:37.00,Default,,0,0,0,,to turn around and go back.\NAddiction is a one way street
Dialogue: 0,1:42:37.00,1:42:41.00,Default,,0,0,0,,it is a total confront with\Nthe absolute necessity
Dialogue: 0,1:42:41.00,1:42:45.00,Default,,0,0,0,,of becoming more conscious\Nin order to live
Dialogue: 0,1:42:45.00,1:42:49.00,Default,,0,0,0,,so that the price of life now\Nitself is that
Dialogue: 0,1:42:49.00,1:42:53.00,Default,,0,0,0,,one has to become more conscious\Nand that is the whole purpose
Dialogue: 0,1:42:53.00,1:42:57.00,Default,,0,0,0,,in consciousness then of\Nthe pathway so it is really
Dialogue: 0,1:42:57.00,1:43:01.06,Default,,0,0,0,,a pathway\Na consciousness pathway
Dialogue: 0,1:43:01.06,1:43:05.06,Default,,0,0,0,,the whole purpose of addiction then is\Nit is a way in which
Dialogue: 0,1:43:05.06,1:43:09.13,Default,,0,0,0,,one is forced\Ndespite oneself to become conscious
Dialogue: 0,1:43:09.13,1:43:13.13,Default,,0,0,0,,to own the truth about oneself\Nto a much greater degree
Dialogue: 0,1:43:13.13,1:43:17.13,Default,,0,0,0,,or one dies\Nin the process and therefore
Dialogue: 0,1:43:17.13,1:43:21.16,Default,,0,0,0,,it is a very powerful\Ncommitment it is really in a way
Dialogue: 0,1:43:21.16,1:43:25.16,Default,,0,0,0,,a long shot because\Nyou either make it you either become more conscious
Dialogue: 0,1:43:25.16,1:43:29.16,Default,,0,0,0,,or you go out the bottom of the box\Nand at the villa they talk about
Dialogue: 0,1:43:29.16,1:43:33.16,Default,,0,0,0,,going out the bottom of the box\Nand this last week somebody else went out the bottom of the box
Dialogue: 0,1:43:33.16,1:43:38.15,Default,,0,0,0,,because the statistics\Nare not all that great
Dialogue: 0,1:43:38.15,1:43:42.15,Default,,0,0,0,,out of 10 million alcoholics\Nthere is 500,000 sober
Dialogue: 0,1:43:42.15,1:43:46.15,Default,,0,0,0,,roughly one out of 20\Nmeans that it is a long shot
Dialogue: 0,1:43:46.15,1:43:50.15,Default,,0,0,0,,in which maybe one out of 20\Nwill own the truth about themselves
Dialogue: 0,1:43:50.15,1:43:54.28,Default,,0,0,0,,to a sufficient degree\Nthat their life will return to them
Dialogue: 0,1:43:54.28,1:43:59.50,Default,,0,0,0,,so the 12th step\Nthen gives away what the purpose
Dialogue: 0,1:43:59.50,1:44:03.50,Default,,0,0,0,,the whole purpose\Nthe end the goal of addiction
Dialogue: 0,1:44:03.50,1:44:07.62,Default,,0,0,0,,is and that is to become more conscious\Nsee you can't change
Dialogue: 0,1:44:07.62,1:44:11.62,Default,,0,0,0,,your mind once you are an addicted\Nperson you cannot become
Dialogue: 0,1:44:11.62,1:44:15.62,Default,,0,0,0,,unaddicted once you have\Nexperienced this energy state
Dialogue: 0,1:44:15.62,1:44:19.66,Default,,0,0,0,,there is no way to remove\Nit from ones memory
Dialogue: 0,1:44:19.66,1:44:23.66,Default,,0,0,0,,ones alignment with the returning\Nto that state the desire to
Dialogue: 0,1:44:23.66,1:44:28.20,Default,,0,0,0,,return to that state\Nits impossible to replace that state
Dialogue: 0,1:44:28.20,1:44:32.20,Default,,0,0,0,,with anything else because anything else\Nis of a much lesser degree
Dialogue: 0,1:44:32.20,1:44:37.80,Default,,0,0,0,,a much lesser degree\Nthe desire to return to that state
Dialogue: 0,1:44:37.80,1:44:42.31,Default,,0,0,0,,then becomes that which\Nruns the person
Dialogue: 0,1:44:42.31,1:44:46.31,Default,,0,0,0,,so we tell people\Nat the villa that
Dialogue: 0,1:44:46.31,1:44:50.31,Default,,0,0,0,,what it is you sought you don't have to be ashamed of\Nwhat you sought
Dialogue: 0,1:44:50.31,1:44:54.31,Default,,0,0,0,,was the same thing that all the saints\Nand everyone else has sought
Dialogue: 0,1:44:54.31,1:44:58.44,Default,,0,0,0,,to experience that great\Nstate within oneself
Dialogue: 0,1:44:58.44,1:45:03.14,Default,,0,0,0,,the presence within\Nthat which is the truth
Dialogue: 0,1:45:03.14,1:45:07.14,Default,,0,0,0,,what you have to know is that\Nwhat's wrong with drugs is
Dialogue: 0,1:45:07.14,1:45:11.30,Default,,0,0,0,,they don't work\Nit's not because they're wrong
Dialogue: 0,1:45:11.30,1:45:15.30,Default,,0,0,0,,it's not because they're destructive\Nit's just that they do not work that's all
Dialogue: 0,1:45:15.30,1:45:19.37,Default,,0,0,0,,they work up to a certain point\Nand then once the energy fuel reverses
Dialogue: 0,1:45:19.37,1:45:23.37,Default,,0,0,0,,they do not work so the reason to give up drugs\Nand alcohol is frankly
Dialogue: 0,1:45:23.37,1:45:27.46,Default,,0,0,0,,that they no longer work\Nthey don't work
Dialogue: 0,1:45:27.46,1:45:31.46,Default,,0,0,0,,and now that you know what it is you're addicted to\Nyou don't have to change your direction at all
Dialogue: 0,1:45:31.46,1:45:35.46,Default,,0,0,0,,your goal before\Nwhat you sought was to experience
Dialogue: 0,1:45:35.46,1:45:39.46,Default,,0,0,0,,this higher energy state\Nso you don't have to change your direction
Dialogue: 0,1:45:39.46,1:45:43.46,Default,,0,0,0,,you only have to change the means of getting there\Nyou only have to change
Dialogue: 0,1:45:43.46,1:45:47.46,Default,,0,0,0,,the means of getting there\Nso that now you own it yourself
Dialogue: 0,1:45:47.46,1:45:51.46,Default,,0,0,0,,so that as you return\Nto that state
Dialogue: 0,1:45:51.46,1:45:55.46,Default,,0,0,0,,it's because of what you are\Nit is not something out there
Dialogue: 0,1:45:55.46,1:45:59.46,Default,,0,0,0,,it's merely the awareness of what you are\Nso that
Dialogue: 0,1:45:59.46,1:46:05.67,Default,,0,0,0,,that state now stems and comes from\Nwithin yourself
Dialogue: 0,1:46:05.67,1:46:09.67,Default,,0,0,0,,as people go through a confront\Nyou know a confront with the facts
Dialogue: 0,1:46:09.67,1:46:13.67,Default,,0,0,0,,about their addiction they go through these\Nvarious experiences
Dialogue: 0,1:46:13.67,1:46:17.67,Default,,0,0,0,,they very often come in\Nin the bottom state of despondency
Dialogue: 0,1:46:17.67,1:46:21.67,Default,,0,0,0,,and everybody pours\Nenergy into them in which state
Dialogue: 0,1:46:21.67,1:46:25.67,Default,,0,0,0,,often they start to cry\Nat the grief over their experience
Dialogue: 0,1:46:25.67,1:46:29.67,Default,,0,0,0,,to find yourself committed\Nto find yourself at the bottom of the box
Dialogue: 0,1:46:29.67,1:46:33.67,Default,,0,0,0,,to find that all that you have valued\Nhas been lost and taken away
Dialogue: 0,1:46:33.67,1:46:37.67,Default,,0,0,0,,the person goes into grief\Ngrief over the realization
Dialogue: 0,1:46:37.67,1:46:41.67,Default,,0,0,0,,that they are addicted\Ngrief over the realization that they have
Dialogue: 0,1:46:41.67,1:46:46.12,Default,,0,0,0,,what seems to them\Nis an impossible problem
Dialogue: 0,1:46:46.12,1:46:50.12,Default,,0,0,0,,and out of that comes the fear\Nto help the person through the fear
Dialogue: 0,1:46:50.12,1:46:54.12,Default,,0,0,0,,of what the consequences of this addiction are\Nand move them up into desiring
Dialogue: 0,1:46:54.12,1:46:58.18,Default,,0,0,0,,something better for themselves\Nto move themselves
Dialogue: 0,1:46:58.18,1:47:02.18,Default,,0,0,0,,to move them up into anger\Nto use that anger to move them into pride
Dialogue: 0,1:47:02.18,1:47:06.18,Default,,0,0,0,,to move them into courage\Nand so the person can be moved
Dialogue: 0,1:47:06.18,1:47:10.25,Default,,0,0,0,,out of the bottom of the box\Nand we will see later
Dialogue: 0,1:47:10.25,1:47:14.25,Default,,0,0,0,,a social phenomena which demonstrates\Nthese principles extremely well
